title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese in large mixer bowl until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Top with your desired amount of pie filling.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cut celery and onions.
Add pepper and bring to boil.
Add quartered tomatoes.
Cook until tender and strain.
Return to pot and add remainder of ingredients.
Bring to a hard boil.
Boil about 5 to 10 minutes. Put in cans or jars.

title: caramels
directions: Mix in a large heavy pot and start cooking at medium high temperature.
Stir continuously.
When mixture comes to full boil, continue to stir and cook for 8 minutes.
Having pregreased a 9 x 13 x 1/2-inch cookie sheet, pour in cooked mixture.
Allow to set until cooled and cut into desired sizes and wrap in wax paper.

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: Cool cake in refrigerator.
When cool put strawberries between layers with some juice on top.
Let this set so the juice will seep into the cake.

title: graham cracker praline nut cookies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and pecans. Boil for 3 minutes over medium heat. Stir occasionally. Spread crackers on large cookie sheet. Spread mixture onto crackers. Bake 6 minutes at 350°. Cool on waxed paper.

title: jelly muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg until smooth, then add milk and oil.
Make hollow in center of flour mixture and add egg mixture. Fill muffin pans 1/3 full and add a small amount of jelly to each in the center, then fill with batter 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve piping hot!

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and 1/4 cup water together for 5 minutes. Set aside and cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender. Mix all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Crust:
Cut butter into flour until well blended.
Add walnuts.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: dry bean soup
directions: Wash beans, place in large kettle, cover with water; add 2 tablespoons salt and soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts water, ham hock or ground beef which has been browned and fat removed. Cook all day in crockpot or simmer on low heat in kettle.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer at least 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a nonstick loaf pan. Top with ketchup.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.
Drain excess juice after 30 minutes and before serving.

title: sausage and sour cream stuffing
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Drain and set aside.
Cut bread into cubes in large bowl.
Add prepared vegetables and spices.
Mix in sausage and chicken broth until moist.
Then add sour cream.
Mix until blended well.
Put into turkey or bake in large casserole at 375° for 1 hour.

title: spinach sandwiches
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate 24 hours before using. Sandwiches can be made up 2 days before using.
Refrigerate in airtight containers with damp paper towel.
Pumpernickel or rye bread is suggested.

title: glazed apple cookies
directions: Cream
together
butter,
sugar
and
eggs until light. Sift together
the flour, salt, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir half dry ingredients into creamed mix.
Stir in apples,
nuts
and raisins.
Add remaining dry ingredients and milk; mix well.
Drop from tablespoon onto greased baking sheet
1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove
to cooling
rack
and	while still warm spread with a glaze.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: homemade cereal
directions: Place oats in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Stir until thoroughly coated.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°, stirring every 3 to 5 minutes until uniformly golden.
Do not overbake.
Let cool in pan, stirring every once in awhile to break up.
Chopped raisins, dates or other dried fruits may be added after cereal is cooled.
Store in tight container in cool place.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: fluffy orange pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; press firmly on bottom and up side of rim of a 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.

title: antipasto of scampi shrimp hors d'oeuvre
directions: Make a stiff mayonnaise with egg yolk, the juice of lemon, salt and olive oil.
Combine it with heavy cream or thick soured cream called "Chef style", brandy and tomato ketchup.
Boil, cool, peel and devein shrimp.
Combine them with the mayonnaise.
Line bottom of large serving dish with a finely shredded chicory, using the tender leaves from the heart.
Place shrimp over this and chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Can be served in individual small dishes as a first course.

title: gourmet crab dressing
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven and add onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute until soft and clear.
Add Ro-Tel and soup. Cook 5 minutes.
Add crab meat and shrimp; season to taste.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add green onion, parsley, pimentos and rice; mix well. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs or cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: peas, onions and radishes
directions: Cut onion in 1-inch pieces.
Slice each radish lengthwise in half.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot margarine or butter, cook onion, stirring occasionally, until golden and tender.
Add radishes, salt and pepper; cook over medium heat until radishes are golden.
Stir in sugar and 2 tablespoons water. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 5 minutes, or until radishes are tender-crisp.
Stir in peas; heat through.
Garnish with radish leaves.
Very good with chicken or roast beef.
Really good.

title: no-bake coconut cake
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
In saucepan, combine egg yolks with flour; stir until smooth.
Add salt and sugar; gradually stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until custard coats back of spoon.
Stir gelatin mixture into hot custard.
Refrigerate until cool, about 1 hour.
Tear cake into large uneven pieces.
Use half of custard over and around cake pieces; sprinkle with half of coconut.
Repeat.
Whip the cream with sugar.
Spread on top of cake and sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add crushed or chopped garlic and chopped onion. Add tomatoes, sauce and seasoning. Let simmer. Cook lasagna noodles and let set in cold water until ready to use. Using a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or casserole dish, alternate layers of noodles, sauce mix, Mozzarella, cottage and Parmesan cheeses (2 layers). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: aunt kat's squash and matoes
directions: Simmer squash, onions, tomatoes, butter or margarine and water until tender or done with lid to cover.
Cut pan off.
Put cheese over mixture and cover until melted very well.

title: rocky road cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Line 24 muffin cups with paper or foil liners. Prepare batter as box directs. Add remaining ingredients. Stir until well blended. Spoon into lined cups. Bake 20 to 22 minutes until a wooden pick inserted in center of cupcakes comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack 5 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack to cool completely.

title: baked cranberry sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, mix cranberries, sugar and water.
Cover dish with foil and bake for 50 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cranberries pop. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: grandma's pumpkin bread
directions: Beat sugar and oil together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add pumpkin.
Sift flour with dry ingredients and add alternately with water.
Grease bread pans and fill with batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Brown onion in small amount of oil; add hamburger meat. Season with garlic, pepper and salt.
Add tomato sauce and chili powder; mix well.
Simmer 15 minutes, covered.
Add kidney beans. Pour into greased casserole.

title: chicken breasts with wild mushrooms and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Soak sun-dried tomatoes in bowl with wine for 30 minutes.
In a large skillet, heat oil and cook the mushrooms and garlic briefly. Transfer to a plate.

In a skillet, cook dredged chicken until browned. To the skillet, add the tomatoes/wine mixture. Cook about 1 minute. Add the mushroom mix, lemon rind and fines herbes and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir in cream and simmer mixture for 1 minute. Add the cooked chicken. Heat through and serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding fruit last.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Other fruit can be used.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates; add boiling water.
Let stand until cool.
Beat egg with salt, sugar, butter, nuts and vanilla; then mix well with the dates and water.
To the flour, add baking powder and sift together.
Add to first mixture and blend thoroughly.
Turn batter into a generously greased loaf pan, and bake in a moderate oven as directed.
Time:
50 to 55 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients
in a large bowl.
After gently mixing the ingredients, place
in	a
large
13 x 11-inch pan. Top with grated Cheddar cheese
and	bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: The sauce should be rather thin
at the start as evaporation adds to the richness.
Do not add sugar or soda to the sauce.
To lessen the acid taste, long slow cooking and the addition of meat will remove all trace of acid.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook sausage and steak in skillet until browned.
Drain well. Set aside.
Heat oil in large Dutch oven.
Add flour and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture turns copper color (8 minutes).
Stir in onion, celery, half of green onion, garlic and parsley.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomato sauce and seasoning.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir meat in and remaining green onions.
Cook until heated.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Add rice and mix well.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt oleo in large frying pan.
Add sugar and blend.
Add dates and cook until sugar is completely absorbed into dates.
Add date mixture, a little at a time, to beaten eggs.
Blend.
Put into skillet and simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, salt and Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls into bowl of coconut and coat.
Put on waxed paper and chill.
Freezes well.

title: *quick and easy gingerbread
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with hot water, beating until smooth. Bake in a greased 6 x 10-inch or 9 x 9-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for about 40 minutes.
This is especially good served warm.
Makes 9 servings.

title: tex-mex cornbread salad
directions: Crumble 1/2 prepared cornbread into bottom of large serving bowl.
Top with 1/2 beans.
In another bowl combine tomatoes, onion, green pepper and jalapeno peppers; blend well.
Spread half of vegetable mixture over beans.
Sprinkle with half the bacon and half the cheese.
Stir together the salsa and sour cream in small bowl.
Spread half dressing over cheese.
Repeat layering procedure with remaining cornbread, beans, vegetables, bacon, cheese and dressing.
Cover tightly.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and flour.
Set aside.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter, stirring well.
Line 1 3/4-inch muffin pans with miniature paper liners.
Spoon 1 teaspoon of crumb mixture into each liner.
Gently press into bottom.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add salt and flour.
Add lemon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add 7-Up.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add margarine, onion, soup, egg and stuffing mix.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese on top.
Put remaining mixture into dish. Sprinkle top with other cheese and some stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease	9-inch	pie
dish
and	spread cranberries over bottom.
Sprinkle
walnuts and 1/2 cup sugar over cranberries. Mix together
the
eggs, 1 cup sugar, flour, almond flavoring and margarine.	Beat
batter
until
smooth
and
pour	over berries. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 325° or until brown.
Cool; cut
in pieces
and
serve	warm.
If pie is cool, serve with whipped cream.

title: the best caesar salad
directions: Add garlic to oil and let stand several hours.
Heat 1/4 cup garlic oil in a small skillet and saute croutons until browned on all sides.
Set aside.

title: pickled okra
directions: Mix ingredients together and bring to a boil and pour over okra in pint jars.
Seal with two piece lids while mixture is hot. Makes 24 pints.

title: mrs. nixon's hot chicken salad
directions: Cook eggs first, then combine all ingredients, except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place combined ingredients in large rectangular casserole dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until browned and bubbly hot.
Serves 8.

title: cocoa light cake
directions: Beat first 8 ingredients on medium 2 minutes.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans or a 13 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until done. Use any kind of frosting.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Note:
Dream whip is good - keeps well for awhile in refrigerator, after, if not all eaten right away.

title: garden taco rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except rice and cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat.
Fluff.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: pecan pie number 1
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, butter and vinegar.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Cool slightly.
Stir eggs (beat), then stir into mixture. (Be sure mixture has cooled enough so eggs will not cook.)
Add nuts and nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 300° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: potato casserole #1
directions: Cubed ham may be added, if desired.

title: mama's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill thoroughly before eating.
Freezes well.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Use devil's food layers.
Melt marshmallows; add milk in top of double boiler.
Put in sugar and coconut; boil 3 minutes. Spread on layers.

title: angel frost
directions: In a blender place lemonade, milk, frozen strawberries and ice cream.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Garnish with fresh strawberries if desired and serve.

title: baked pork tenderloin
directions: Salt the tenderloins.
Top each with a few onion flakes, 1 tablespoon Cheez Whiz and a generous dollop of sour cream.
Bake about 2 hours at 350°.
Cover pan to start.
Uncover if needed to brown.
These warm up well if there are leftovers.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake; add 1/2 cup coconut to batter.
Cool; poke holes with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour coconut milk over cake.
Cool completely!
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with coconut.

title: anne's french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Refrigerate a few days before using.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Beat buttermilk and eggs in bowl first, then add buttermilk. Mix 1/2 cup flour, soda and salt, then add another 1/2 cup flour and add to milk and egg mixture.
Test for thickness on griddle. (Add milk or flour to thicken or thin.)

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Measure flour, then alternate flour and milk.
Stir in almond and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well.
Grease Bundt cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Do not preheat oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook in saucepan the strawberry pie filling, chunk pineapple, sugar and cornstarch until it thickens.
Take it off heat.
Add the strawberry Jell-O and red food coloring.
Let cool.
Add the bananas.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped pecans.

title: cheery coffee cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Set aside.
Combine 1/2 cup dry cake mix, yeast, flour, eggs and 2/3 cup warm water.
Beat 2 minutes. Spread dough in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine rest of dry cake mix with margarine.
Set aside.
Spoon pie filling over dough in pan.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and then crumble topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in ingredients in order given (except cheese).
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Spoon into 9-inch square baking dish and dot with strips of cheese, arranged in diamond shapes.
Broil until cheese is melted and then garnish with olives in center of diamonds.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: flavorful rice
directions: *If you substitute wild rice, use the whole box and add 1/4 to 1/2 cup extra white rice and a little extra water or cut back on the onion soup because of the flavoring packet in the wild rice. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix Crisco and 3/4 cup sugar in large bowl.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over sugar and Crisco; stir until melted and set aside.
Beat eggs in a
cup and set aside.
Mix dry yeast into large bowl with Crisco and sugar; stir.
Fold in flour, a little at a time, until all is mixed.
Set dough into refrigerator for at least 4 hours.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Add your cranberry sauce. Mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour in 9 x 11-inch Pyrex dish and freeze.

title: congo squares
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Beat butter or margarine together with brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each egg.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat in reserved flour mixture and when well combined, fold in chocolate bits and nuts.
Spread batter in prepared dish, smoothing the top. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until top looks dry.
Let cool completely and cut into squares.
Makes about 4 dozen squares.

title: rich coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
While cake is not, mix sweetened condensed milk with cream of coconut milk.
Make small holes in cake with fork and pour mixture over cake.
Spread it until it soaks in.
Frost with whipped topping and sprinkle with shredded coconut.
Also good if whipped topping is not used.

title: lemon chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.

Make a well and add in this order the oil, egg yolks, water, lemon peel and vanilla. Beat with spoon until smooth. Beat the egg whites and cream of tartar in a large mixer bowl on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over beaten whites, gently folding with rubber spatula just until blended.
Pour into ungreased 10 x 14-inch tube pan. Bake until top springs back when touched lightly, about 1 1/4 hours.
Invert pan on funnel.
Let hang until cake is cold. Remove from pan. Frost with Lemon Butter Frosting.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: You will need 1 punch bowl or a large container.

title: double sherbet punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Before serving, add 1 cup pineapple sherbet and 1 cup orange sherbet.

title: gourmet coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Brew as desired at 1 1/2 times normal strength.
Mixture may be stored in airtight container in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Makes 14 servings.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a gallon size ice cream freezer.
I prefer "Slice" mandarin orange.
Other flavors may be used.

title: julie's caesar salad
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat, add 1 tablespoon olive oil and garlic.
Add bread cubes and saute 3 to 5 minutes or until browned to taste.
Remove and set aside.
Combine lettuce, cheese and pepper in a large bowl and toss.
Combine 1/2 cup olive oil and remaining ingredients in a jar, cover tightly and shake well to blend.
Pour desired amount (makes more than you need) over lettuce and toss to coat.
Add croutons and toss gently.
Serve immediately.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Rinse tube pan in cold water and invert while
mixing cake.
Beat egg whites.
When they begin to
foam, add cream of tartar.
Continue beating until stiff. With wooden spoon, fold in sugar, then flour to which salt has been
added. Add
vanilla
and pour in an ungreased tube pan. Bake
in
the middle of oven approximately 45 minutes or until done.
Let cool in inverted pan.

title: norma's banana muffins
directions: Mix bananas, sugar and slightly beaten egg.
Add Crisco and sifted dry ingredients.
Mix lightly and place in muffin tins lined with paper baking cups.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cat's pepsi ham
directions: Make slices in the ham all around it, about 1-inch thick.
In a saucepan, cook Pepsi, brown sugar and pineapple on medium to high heat until it begins to thicken just slightly.
Place ham in cake pan.
Pour in between slices of ham and on top of ham.
Lay bacon on top of ham.
Basting with juices, bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: spicy shrimp and pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions and rinse with cold water.
Add shrimp, chopped vegetables, seasonings and mayonnaise/water dressing until coated.
Garnish with lemon slices and paprika.
Chill.
Serve with lots of liquid refreshments, as this dish can be quite hot!!

title: molasses ginger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon, and cloves together in medium bowl.
Beat 1 cup sugar and the butter and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add egg, molasses and orange peel; beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and beat until combined.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in remaining 1/4 cup sugar and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Add water-soda mixture and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder, salt and oats.
Add to creamed mixture and blend. Add gumdrops and coconut.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crisp baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken quarters into buttermilk, and set aside briefly while you crush cereal flakes.
Dip chicken into flakes and lay chicken on a flat pan or cookie sheet far enough apart so that pieces do not touch each other, skin side up. Bake for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
This sauce is delicious on ice cream or cake.
You can also cut your cake, put ice cream in between layers and put chocolate sauce on top.

title: oatmeal cookies(crisp)
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, vanilla and egg yolks.
Mix in flour, soda, salt and oatmeal.
Add nuts and raisins if desired.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° or until brown.
Grease cookie sheets.

title: crawfish etouffee-the real way
directions: Saute vegetables in butter, continually stirring.
Add crawfish and saute for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Add the cream of mushroom soup and red pepper.
Add salt to taste.
Add paprika if desired for darker color purposes only.
Do not add water.
Cook uncovered for approximately 15 minutes on low to medium heat or longer on low heat to obtain a creamy sauce.
Serve over rice with French bread.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni bites
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into small squares.
(Can be frozen.)

title: chewy creamy pralines
directions: Blend all ingredients, except pecans.
Cook to soft ball stage.
When tested in cool water, add pecans and beat immediately until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly buttered cookie sheet.

title: frosty fruit loaf
directions: Drain fruit cocktail (save liquid); dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add fruit liquid.
Cool until syrupy.
Mix mayonnaise with yogurt.
Add to jello (blend well).
Fold in drained fruit cocktail; chill until set.
May use other jello and yogurt flavors.
Also may use other fruits, peaches, crushed pineapple, etc.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together onto waxed paper the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add walnuts.
In mixing bowl, beat egg.
Add cranberry sauce and shortening.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until just blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Place noodles in boiling water until cooked. Put the tuna in a casserole dish.
Add the cooked noodles and "Fines" herbs.
Mix well. Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: doris' brownies
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine cocoa, margarine and water; cook until it reaches the boiling point.
Add the cooked mixture to the blended batter. Pour into a sheet pan (10 x 15-inch).
Bake for 23 minutes at 350°.
Frost.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in nuts and marshmallows.
Sprinkle extra nuts on top.
Chill 2 hours.

title: french onion soup
directions: Pour bouillon stock in crock-pot, cover and cook on high. Cook onions with butter slow in skillet.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Uncover and add salt, flour, sugar and wine.
Stir well and add to crock-pot.
Cook for 6 to 8 hours on low.
Serve bread topped with cheese slices and cover with French Onion Soup.

title: marinated tomatoes and cucumbers
directions: In large bowl mix well all ingredients. Cover and chill at least one hour to blend flavors. Makes about 3-1/2 c. or 6 servings.

title: fall dinner in a pumpkin
directions: Using a sharp knife, cut lid from pumpkin and scoop out pumpkin seeds and excess membrane with a scraping tool.
In a large skillet, combine ground beef, chopped green pepper, chopped celery, and chopped onion and cook over medium heat until ground beef is browned.
Add next seven ingredients to skillet.
Mix well and place mixture into pumpkin cavity.
Place lid on pumpkin. Place pumpkin on a foil-lined cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Just before serving, embellish pumpkin by placing (with toothpicks) black olives to make eyes, a steamed carrot to make a nose, and whole cloves to make a mouth.
Use parsley leaves to make hair around the opening.

title: green rice
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in skillet.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Pour in skillet and bring to boil.
Grease casserole dish.
Pour rice in dish.
Add pepper to taste.
Mix pepper, rice and parsley in covered casserole dish.
Pour skillet ingredients over rice and cook 20 minutes at 325°.
Fluff and cook, uncovered, an additional 20 minutes.

title: caldo verde(green soup)
directions: In saucepan, boil water, onion, pepperoni and oil for 1/2 hour.
Add cabbage and reduce to soft boil for 15 minutes.
Add potato flakes slowly, stirring constantly.
For thicker soup, add more flakes.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: ginny's sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks and sour cream. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix together the sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts and sprinkle on the cake.
Dot with extra butter. Bake at 325° for one hour.
Allow to cool in pan for 15 minutes before turning out.

title: chocolate  dream
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13 inch dish according to recipe on the box. Cool. Cut into 1 inch pieces. Prepare chocolate pudding according to package directions. Layer twice in trifle compote: Cake pieces, Heath bar crumbs, chocolate pudding and cool whip. On top of the last Cool Whip, sprinkle some Heath Bars crumbs.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; add eggs.
Mix flour, cream of tartar and soda together and add to first mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Roll soft batter into size of walnut. Roll ball in granulated sugar.
Dip bottom of glass into sugar and flatten ball.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into small balls.
Chill thoroughly.
Bake 10-15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie crust as directed.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over bottom of pie crust.
Top with pecan halves.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar, syrup, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Garnish with whipped cream and drizzle melted chocolate chips over cream. Refrigerate.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all together in bowl. Turn into casserole. Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Place ground beef and pork sausage in a large pan on stove. Add chopped onions and green pepper. Stir.
Let this cook for a few minutes. Add the rest of the ingredients and boil for 1 to 2 minutes. Water may have to be added if sauce is too thick.

title: doughnuts and holes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Lightly beat eggs, sugar, milk and butter together and combine.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a Pyrex baking dish.
Place 2 tablespoons margarine on each breast.
Put mushrooms on top. Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Add the sherry and cover with foil.
Cook in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Time may vary, depending on the size of breasts and individual ovens.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften the yeast in warm water. Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm. Add 1 cup flour. Beat well. Beat in yeast mixture and egg. Add remaining flour; mix well. Place in greased bowl and cover. Store in refrigerator for 2 hours or until needed. Shape roll 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving. Roll out, shape and let rise.
Cook in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Bring water, chicken, celery, carrots, onion, bouillon granules and 1 tablespoon parsley to a boil in large saucepan. Reduce heat; simmer for 1 hour.
While chicken cooks, mix remaining ingredients except chicory (endive or spinach) and 1 egg.
Shape into 1/2-inch meatballs.
Cover and refrigerate until needed.
Remove chicken, celery and carrots from broth.
When cool enough to handle, remove skin and bones from chicken and discard. Cut chicken into 1/2-inch pieces.
Slice carrots and celery into 1/4-inch pieces.
Return chicken and vegetables to broth.
Add meatballs.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 5 minutes, until meatballs are done.
(This much could be done ahead of time.)
Stir greens into soup; bring to a boil.
Beat remaining egg; pour slowly into soup, stirring constantly.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans. Mix as for a pie crust. Pat into a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (do not brown). Let cool. Cream 1 cup powdered sugar with cream cheese. Mix well; fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip (thawed). Mix pudding with milk; beat until thick. Put cream cheese mixture on top of crust. Add pudding mixture as next layer. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top. You may also sprinkle with nuts.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Place sliced fruit in 8-inch square baking dish; sprinkle with lemon juice and sugar.
Combine flour, oats, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until crumbs are golden brown and fruit is tender when pierced with knife.

title: fabulous  onion soup
directions: In a large heavy pot melt 2 Tbsp. butter with oil over medium heat.
Stir in onions, sugar and salt.
Cook stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 10 minutes.
Remove lid and cook 15 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining butter to pot.
Cook stirring occasionally for 15 minutes or until onions are caramelized and very soft.
Stir in flour and cook 3 minutes.
Stir in broth, sherry, thyme and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Preheat broiler.
Lightly toast bread slices.
Ladle soup into 6 ovenproof bowls and arrange on baking sheet.
Put enough bread on top of each serving. Sprinkle bread with shredded cheese.
Broil until cheese is bubbly and golden.
Serve hot.

title: maw-maw's golden wedding punch
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: oatmeal walnut cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 20 minutes.
Water will have been absorbed.
Combine eggs and brown sugar in large bowl; beat with electric mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Beat in margarine and lemon rind.
Sift flour, baking soda and cinnamon onto waxed paper.
Add to egg and brown sugar mixture.
Add oatmeal; mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Turn batter into a sprayed with Pam 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve liquid.
Cut pineapple slices in half.
Drain cherries and cut in half.
Pat fruit with paper towel to make sure they are drained well.

title: osgood pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well and add next 6 ingredients. Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour in two uncooked pie shells. Bake in 300° oven until knife comes out clean.

title: fried softshell crabs
directions: Wash crabs but do not dry.
Whisk eggs, salt and pepper until fluffy
and set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Dip crabs
in flour,
then egg and then into hot oil.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes
on each
side
on
medium-high heat.
Drain on paper towels
and serve
on
platter with lemon wedges, if desired. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Prepare and cook broccoli (if frozen) as on package.
Heat remaining ingredients over medium heat, 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir frequently.
When cheese sauce is all melted and smooth, pour over broccoli.
Makes 4 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef along with onion and drain fat.
Mix in beans, green chilies, tomato sauce, garlic salt and pepper and cook until warm in 8 x 11 baking dish.
Put layer of tortillas, layer of mix, layer of cheese (2 times) and top off with enchilada sauce and black olives.
Cook in microwave 5 to 8 minutes.

title: sloppy joes in a bun
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add ground meat; brown.
Add remaining ingredients. Use only enough crumbs to make mixture hold shape for sandwiches.
Serve on buns.
Makes 25 or more sandwiches.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and butter in bowl; mix well.
Pat in a cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips; spread on peanut butter mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: every day pudding
directions: Mix together and pour over the first mixture in casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped topping. Serve warm or cold.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross with fork prongs.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool for 1 minute before removing from pan.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: no-cook play dough
directions: Add salt to flour in medium sized mixing bowl; mix well.
Add cold water, a tablespoon at a time, to make mixture that is the consistency of pie dough.
Add food coloring a drop at a time until desired color.

title: dirty rice
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered. Stir occasionally.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Dip onion rings in flour, then egg and milk and then the cracker meal.
Fry; only needs to cook a few seconds in hot fat.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add lemon juice.
Cool. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add gelatin and mix well.
Fold whipped cream (Milnot) into gelatin mixture.

title: lil' wienies
directions: Cut hot dogs into four sections. Cut bacon slices into four sections. Roll bacon sections around hot dog sections.
Secure with toothpick. Place in crock-pot and pack brown sugar firmly on top of them. Cook on high for 3 hours.

title: country-fried green tomatoes
directions: Sprinkle tomatoes with sugar; let stand about 15 minutes. Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip tomato slices in mixture. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Brown tomatoes slowly on both sides.
Remove each batch to ovenproof platter and keep hot in oven until all tomatoes are cooked.
Add more butter if needed. For crisp slices, serve as is.
Can add 1/2 cup light cream or dairy half and half to skillet.
Heat, stirring, into drippings and pour over tomatoes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon icebox pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat partially thawed Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk on medium speed until well blended.
Then add lemon juice and yellow food coloring.
Mix well, then pour into graham cracker pie crusts. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Slice and serve.
Very good.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add vanilla.
Add the sifted flour and salt gradually.
Add the nuts.
Form into 1-inch balls. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. While hot, roll the cookies in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in sugar again.

title: collards or turnip salad
directions: Wash greens real good.
Put into a pot of boiling water.
Cook until tender.
Heat some oil or grease in an iron skillet and place greens in the pan.
Add salt to taste and cut up.
Cover and cook on low heat until they are good and tender.

title: filled pizelles
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Blend in oil, flavoring, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat for about 3 minutes.
Cook on hot waffle iron (Italian pizelle iron) by teaspoonful.
When waffle is done, keep as is or shape while hot over a glass custard cup, pressing to fit.
Place another cup on top to hold in place and shape.
Stack to store.
Fill with favorite cream filling or with Rum Cream Filling.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add shortening.
Beat in milk, coffee, vanilla and eggs for 2 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 or 60 minutes.
Bake in two greased and floured 9-inch pans. Use whipped cream icing if you want.

title: chocolate chip treasure cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. In small bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs, flour and baking powder. In large mixer bowl, beat milk and margarine until smooth. Add cracker crumb mixture, mix well. Stir in coconut, chips and walnuts. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 9 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: picnic meatballs
directions: Place frozen meatballs in a crock-pot.
Pour both jars of chili sauce and both jars of grape jelly over top.
Cover and cook on low approximately 5 to 6 hours.
Stir occasionally to coat meatballs with sauce.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken
and
save
broth;
bone
and
cut
up the chicken.
Put
soups,
chilies and onion in a large pan.
Pour in some of the broth, but don't make it too thin.
Add chicken to this mixture and heat through.
Dip tortillas in hot grease and line
bottom
of
casserole
dish, then put a layer of the mixture.
Repeat
until
all
is used.
Bake at 325° until hot and bubbly.

title: corn corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease iron skillet and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all the above.
Bring to a boil and let simmer 30 minutes or longer.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off unpeeled, washed tomatoes.
Save the tops. Squeeze or scoop out the seeds of the tomatoes and reserve the juice.
Sprinkle insides with salt and invert to drain.
Brown meat; drain fat and set aside.
Saute onion and rice in olive oil in heavy skillet over medium heat until rice is translucent and just turning brown.
Combine meat, rice, herbs, cheese and reserved tomato juice.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix butter, soup, sour cream and 1 cup shredded cheese. In 9 x 13 baking dish, pour soup mixture over hash browns. Sprinkle remaining cheese over soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic; saute 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Cook 8 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream cheese; cook 2 minutes. Add 1 cup Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly, until it melts. Pour over hot fettuccine; toss well to coat.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, fresh parsley and pepper.
Makes four 1-cup servings.
Contains 345 calories, 9.75 g fat, 18 mg cholesterol and 401 mg sodium.

title: "grandma's vienna bars"
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken with creamy rice casserole
directions: Pour rice in baking pan (uncooked) to cover bottom at least 1/8 inch.
Dot rice with one of the cans of cream of mushroom soup.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Mix last can with can of water; blend smooth.
Pour over all.
Place in oven at 350°.
Check water periodically (add if needed).
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Needs a little attention.
Great for big groups.

title: sweet popcorn
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Pour over popped popcorn.

title: lasagna
directions: In a heavy pan, lightly brown the hamburger and onion.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, parsley, sugar, garlic, pepper, salt and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread a layer of sauce, a layer of noodles and a layer of cheeses.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used and pan is full.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes, until brown and bubbling.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Combine orange juice and rind or crushed pineapple (small can) and beaten egg; pour over dry mixture.
Stir to dampen and fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Season hamburger meat and cook with onion until meat is browned.
Add barbecue sauce and pork and beans.
Stir well to mix.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are done.

title: cabbage favorite
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Drain well.
Layer in Dutch oven ground chuck and onion, cabbage, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Pour just enough V-8 juice over mixture to reach top of layers.
Cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together flavoring with almond extract to taste.
Serve with a variety of fruit.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Pour into two 8-inch graham cracker pie shells.
Pour pie filling over the 2 pies.
Add sugar on top of cherry filling.

title: spiced punch
directions: Combine ingredients in 4 quart pan and simmer.
Serve warm.

title: garlic-tomato
directions: Cut cloves of garlic and tomatoes.
Cover with Italian salad dressing in a bowl, such as a Tupperware.
Turn bowl upside down every hour or so for 8 to 24 hours.

title: granola
directions: Plus nuts, rolled grains, dates, etc.

title: carrot bread
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bake at 325° in well-greased bread tin.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked crust and bake at 375° until custard is set or knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature; whip until fluffy. Gradually add Eagle Brand milk.
Continue to beat until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into crust and chill 2 to 3 hours before garnishing top with pie filling.

title: zwieback
directions: Place bread
on oven rack.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 to 3 hours, until crispy dry.
Thinner slices dry more quickly.

title: louisiana sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells for 1 hour at 350°.
Cover and steam with another pie plate while cooking.
Top with topping the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Marinate boneless, skinless chicken breasts in Catalina dressing at least 1 hour.
(Better if 2 to 4 hours.)
Cook chicken on grill until done.
Serve with salad and baked potato.

title: frozen pina colada
directions: Mix together and put into plastic containers and freeze. Spoon into glass; add ice cubes and pour Squirt to fill glass.

title: sweet tooth breakfast
directions: Warm waffles in toaster, according to package directions. Spread each waffle with jam.
Thickly spread each waffle with ice cream and make a sandwich with waffles.
Eat immediately.

title: cranberry spritzer
directions: Combine cranberry juice, Sauterne and Triple Sec in a pitcher. Just before serving, add club soda.
Serve over crushed ice. Yield:
1 1/2 quarts.

title: homemade yellow cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O with 9 cups boiling water.
In separate bowl, dissolve 4 cups sugar in 8 cups boiling water.
Let both mixtures cool completely.
Then combine the two mixtures and to this add the concentrated lemon juice and pineapple juice; stir well.
Freeze in large Ziploc bags (freezer type).
It is best to put it in four bags (about 10 cups in each).
Then you use two bags per 1 quart Sprite.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and flour.
Beat well.
Then add chips and nuts. Make little balls, then flatten out with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into patties.
Fry in small amount of oil until brown on both sides.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Whip together.
Dip Granny Smith apples into it.

title: foolproof apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in a bowl; let stand 10 minutes. Combine flour and the next 4 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine oil, vanilla and egg white; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in apple mixture.
Spoon batter into an 8-inch square baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted comes out clean. Cool completely in pan on a wire rack.
Yields 9 servings. (Serving size is a 2 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch piece.)

title: meat & sausage
directions: Brown chopped meat and sausage until lightly browned; set aside.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Soak cucumbers in salt water.
Drain well.
Mix sour cream, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour over cucumbers.
Chill before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg.
Heat with taco seasoning according to package directions.
Let cool.
Add to next 5 ingredients.
Right before serving, add chips (crumbled).
Pour dressing over all and mix.

title: crabbies
directions: Blend ingredients and spread on muffin halves. Freeze open. When frozen, stack.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut stew meat and fry in pan on medium heat until all the water boils out.
When water boils out, brown meat and add a little oil, onions and mushrooms.
Turn heat down and brown.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and garlic salt. Drain when browned.
Stir in beans.
In saucepan, cream together soups, milk and taco sauce.
Grease 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Line dish with Doritos.
Pour in 1/2 meat and bean mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese.
Add layer of Doritos.
Layer on rest of meat mixture.
Pour on soup.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Add rest of cheese.
Bake another 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: grandma's molasses candy
directions: Cook molasses, sugar and vinegar until crunchy or brittle when dropped into cold water.
Stir in a pinch of baking soda and 3 cups of chopped nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
When cold, break into bite size pieces.

title: pecan monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Layer in greased Bundt pan.
Combine butter and brown sugar in bowl; stir until well blended.
Drizzle over biscuits. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown. Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Boil all ingredients for 20 minutes.
Take from stove and stir in 1 large box strawberry Jell-O.
Pour into jars.
Seal.
To be kept in the refrigerator.

title: coqui
directions: Combine the coconut cream, evaporated milk, condensed milk, egg yolks and vanilla in blender.
Blend at high speed for 30 seconds (or until smooth).
Add the cinnamon and blend for a few seconds.
Refrigerate the coqui into chilled parfait or punch glasses.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg on top.

title: refrigerator strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add strawberries. Put into graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix all of the above and shape into a mold or loaf. Then refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 12 hours on high.
Stir occasionally to break up or shred meat.

title: country sausage and rice
directions: In large skillet brown sausage and drain well. Stir in rice, celery, carrots, onion and broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally until liquid is absorbed and rice is done.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Bring rhubarb and water to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add sugar and boil at simmer for 20 minutes.
Add strawberry jello. Put in jars and seal with wax.

title: brown rice
directions: Fry onion in margarine until transparent. Add beef broth and consomme. Heat to boiling. Pour in rice. Put in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: linguine with clam sauce
directions: Cook pasta as the label directs.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, over medium heat in hot oil, cook the garlic until lightly browned.
Stir in the bread crumbs and cook until lightly toasted.
Remove the crumbs from the skillet and set aside.
Place the clams and their liquid, the clam juice and the wine in the skillet.
Bring to a boil and cook until the liquid is reduced by 1/3.
Stir in the parsley, salt and pepper.
Drain the pasta and toss with the sauce and bread crumbs.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken and set aside. Save broth.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook vegetables, celery and onion until tender; drain.
Combine cheese, mayonnaise and vegetables.
Put into a 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Combine oleo and cracker crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: christmas breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and bacon.
Mix eggs, milk, crumbled bread and cheese in a large bowl.
Add crumbled sausage and bacon.
Place in 9x13 greased dish.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix cream cheese, vanilla, egg yolk, sugar and lemon juice until smooth; set aside.
Lay 1 package of crescent rolls flat on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pinch seams together.
Spread filling almost to edges.
Lay 2nd package of crescent rolls on counter (sprinkle with flour first); pinch seams together.
Lay on top of filling.
Press edges together.
Brush beaten egg whites on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry holly cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Place butter or oleo in large bowl and beat at low speed to soften.
Blend in grated lemon rind. Mix in dry ingredients; add buttermilk and mix well.
Beat 2 minutes at low speed.
Add eggs and beat 1 minute.
Stir in cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Frost with White Mountain Frosting.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in oiled casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add salad oil and eggs together, then add to dry mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dried peaches
directions: The night before cooking, mix sugar and vinegar with peaches. The following morning, cook on low heat until brown or color of evaporated peaches.
Place in hot jar and seal or freeze.
Makes 7 pints.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Make into balls (about 80-100). Place in covered pan with sauce.

title: new england corn and turkey pie
directions: Place turkey in the bottom of a greased quiche pan.
Beat together eggs, milk and flour.
Add remaining ingredients to egg mixture and pour over the turkey.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Add cheese. Mix with other ingredients.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add milk and oil.
Drop by teaspoonful into deep fat. Makes about 30 or more.

title: tuna salad pockets
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. Spoon into pitas. Yield: 2 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Blend milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Top with pie filling.

title: honey carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of boiling water approximately 5 to 10 minutes (until crisp-tender).
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup carrot liquid.
Combine reserved liquid, honey, butter and brown sugar.
Stir well and pour over carrots.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.

title: dad's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in skillet and saute onion, pecans and mushrooms, if used.
Remove onion and brown chicken lightly in oil.
Place chicken in roasting pan or Dutch oven. Stir all remaining ingredients into frypan, making a gravy.
Stir in sauteed onion.
Pour all over chicken; cover and bake 1 hour or until tender.
If gravy is too thick after baking, dilute with sherry, milk or chicken bouillon.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles with a tossed green salad.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and grease an 8 x 8 pan.
Mix together all ingredients except confectionary sugar, butter, additional peanut butter, vanilla and milk.
Place mixed ingredients in square pan and bake for 25-30 minutes.
Let cool completely before frosting.
Mix together the confectionary sugar, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and milk and spread over cooled bars.

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in a 3-quart bowl the sugar, flour, salt and spices.
Add pumpkin, egg and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted 2 inches from edge comes out clean.

title: poor man's dish
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except Crisco
and tomato juice. Make into small balls.
Brown in skillet
with
Crisco. Place in baking dish with lid.
Pour on enough tomato juice to cover. Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn and
if
dry, add a little water.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Marinate broccoli 1 hour in 1/2 bottle dressing.
Cut pasta into 3 to 4-inch strips, then cook al dente.
Combine ingredients, then toss with dressing and chill several hours. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: campfire biscuit twists(method:  stick)
directions: Stir sugar and cinnamon into biscuit mix.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Divide into 4 equal portions and give to 4 different people.
Roll each portion in floured hands to form a rope.
Roll rope around a skewer in a spiral.
Squeeze ends together.
Hold about 6 inches from coals to cook.
Turn skewer often until dough is lightly browned and thoroughly cooked.
This takes practice but is fun!
Eat with fingers or put on a plate and brush with butter while hot.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Makes 4 servings.

title: traditional baked lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
In large skillet, saute meat, onions, salt and garlic salt; drain off excess fat.
Add spaghetti sauce; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
In greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, layer 3 strips of lasagna, lengthwise, spread on 1/3 meat sauce, 1/3 of Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layering process twice. Sprinkle Romano cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven 35 to 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corned beef and cole slaw
directions: Make the sauce from the first 7 ingredients.
Cook cabbage 10 minutes and drain.
Combine sauce and cabbage and put in casserole dish.
Top with sliced corned beef; sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 400° until dish is hot and crumbs are brown.

title: encharitos
directions: Encharito Sauce:
Cut meat off pork chops and cut up into bite-size pieces.
Boil bones in seasoned water.
Cook pork in small amount of oil and water and season until lightly browned. Add enchilada sauce and equal amount of pork broth or a little more.
Add 1/2 to 1 can of green chiles.
Simmer for a short while, then thicken slightly with cornstarch.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Add all ingredients to bowl and mix well.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Ice with cream cheese icing while still warm.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spread refried beans in bottom of casserole dish.
Scant salsa over refried beans.
Place hamburger mixture over top with Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips or microwave.

title: orange julius
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients.
Process 1/2 minute or until ice is crushed.
If desired, top with a scoop of ice cream.

title: pat's drink thing
directions: Blot artichokes dry on paper towels.
Chop into small pieces. In a medium bowl, whisk together remaining ingredients, blending well.
Stir in artichokes. Cover and refrigerate
for at least one hour to allow flavors to blend. Stir before serving.

title: swedish meat balls in cranberry sauce
directions: Arrange meat balls in open pan and bake at 350°; pour off fat when done.

title: garden pilaf
directions: In a medium bowl, soak bulgur in hot water for 1 hour; drain well.
Add tomato, cucumber, green onion, parsley and cilantro. Toss together and chill.

title: poppy seed tea cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Mix eggs, sugar, milk and oil and beat well. Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add

first mixture to dry ingredients; then add almond extract and imitation butter flavoring and poppy seed and mix well. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, maybe a bit more, 350° (325° for glass loaf dish). Remove from pans immediately after baking.

title: chicken glace
directions: Brown flour and oil.
Boil large chicken until tender; keep broth.
Cool.
Remove skin and cut in small pieces.
Mix chicken and seasonings (all chopped fine) and cook in roux for 15 minutes. Dissolve gelatine and mix with broth and vegetables.
Pour in 2 molds and chill overnight.
Serve in slices with crackers.

title: kathryn's buns
directions: Mix first two ingredients and set aside ten minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients with electric mixer.
Add yeast water mixture and beat.
Then add 4 to 5 cups flour.
Knead until it isn't sticky.
Let stand 20 to 30 minutes.
Shape into loaves or make rolls.
Let double and bake at 400° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil, then add 2 to 3 (12 ounce) cans tomato paste and cook 10 to 20 minutes.

title: golden corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in a two-quart casserole.
Mix sugar and flour and add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° until silver knife comes out clean.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix until clinging.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Put broken pecans in bottom of uncooked shell.
Pour mixture over them and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: wanda's favorite pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed with an electric mixer.
(This takes about 15 minutes.)
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Melt butter in skillet (225°).
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Combine with ingredients until done.

title: oregano browned chicken and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine, lemon and pepper seasoning and ReaLemon juice.
Cut excess skin and fat from chicken, if desired.
Cut potatoes in half.

title: skillet cookies
directions: In 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in sugar and dates; remove from heat.
Stir in egg.
Return to heat. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil for 4 to 6 minutes.
Boil, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Chop vegetables and saute in 2 to 3 tablespoons olive oil (with meat if used) until onion and pepper begin to get soft (or meat is browned).
Add beans, soup, tomato paste and spices and mix well.
Simmer over medium heat, stirring occasionally for 15 to 30 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Prepare cornbread according to box directions and spread cornbread mixture over top of tamale.
Bake at 425° until cornbread is brown on top and done throughout (about 30 to 45 minutes).

title: italian lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion in large deep frypan.
Add mushrooms also. Cook noodles as directed in boiler.
Drain fat off meat mixture. Return meat mixture to heat.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and spaghetti sauce.
Cook and stir ingredients 5 or 10 minutes.
Drain water off noodles.
Layer ingredients:
noodles, meat mixture, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat if necessary.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool some and cut in squares.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: 4 grain walnut bread
directions: Sprinkle oatmeal into the 2 cups boiling water in pan.
Bring to boil again.
In a bowl, place salt, molasses and butter.
Pour oatmeal mixture over this and allow to cool to lukewarm.

title: "chocolate kissed thumbprint cookies"
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet or use Pam.
Beat together margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined oats, flour and 2/3 cup nuts. Beat egg whites with fork.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Dip in egg white; press one side into remaining nuts.
Place nut side up on cookie sheet; press thumb deeply in center of each.
Bake 8 minutes.
Place kiss into each center; return to oven 5 to 7 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: fudge
directions: Combine marshmallow creme, sugar, milk, margarine and salt. Bring to a full boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly!
Remove from heat, add chocolate pieces and stir until all chocolate is melted.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together the beaten eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon; add chopped nuts to first mixture.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Divide batter into each.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Separate buns, then butter and toast under broiler until golden brown.
Spread each half with tuna mixture and return to broiler until golden brown.
Top each half with a slice of tomato and broil until tomato is wilted.
Top each half with a slice of cheese.
Broil until melted.

title: chocolate-strawberry shortcake
directions: Remove the stems from berries; set aside a few perfect berries to garnish the cake.
Crush the rest slightly and sweeten to taste.
Butter a 9-inch round cake pan.
Set the oven at 425°.

title: clam chowder
directions: Grind onions, potatoes, celery and clams.
Put fat in bottom of heavy pot.
Stir in flour.
Add ground mixture, water and seasonings.
Boil just until vegetables are tender.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cornbread mix. Add it last. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Bake 25 minutes at 400°. Serve hot.

title: mexican snowball
directions: Will need an 8 ounce coffee glass.
Mix hot Tequila and Kahula in glass.
Fill with coffee.
Top with whip cream.
Add cinnamon stick as garnish.

title: dirt cake
directions: Bowl 1:
Mix cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: onion and beef microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Put sauce on top of meat loaf and cover with wax paper.
Cook on Roast, or High for 25 to 32 minutes.

title: honey cornmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Grease bottoms only of muffin tin. In large bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and lemon peel.
Mix well.
Add milk, honey, oil and egg; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 13-18 min. or until very light brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Immediately remove from pan.
Best served warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn; reserve liquid.
Mix corn liquid with milk to make a 1/2 cup.
Beat eggs; mix with milk.
Add flour, baking powder and salt with eggs and milk.
Stir in corn.
Mixture should be of a semi-stiff consistency.
If not, add more flour.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot cooking oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: spiced red cabbage
directions: In a saucepan, combine shredded cabbage with all ingredients except apples and sugar.
Cover and cook over moderate heat for 15 minutes, tossing several times so the cabbage will cook evenly. Add apples; toss again.
Cover; cook 5 minutes longer.
Add sugar. If more water is needed during cooking, add 2 or 3 tablespoons but when the dish is done, all moisture should have cooked away. Yield:
6 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: pizza rounds(appetizer)
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Cut cheese in chunks.
Place over meat. Cover and simmer until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Add spices and simmer.
Spoon meat mixture onto round rye bread or small slices party bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown and bubbly.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: honey mustard sauce
directions: Mix together ingredients until well blended.
Serve over ham or roast beef.

title: beverly's hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat with garlic salt.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix meat, macaroni, onion, mushrooms and sauce in casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese of your choice prior to serving.

title: glaze sauce for meat
directions: Brown meat in a hot skillet.
Add the juices and honey; cook until meat reduces down and thickens.
Be careful not to let it burn.
(The juice gives it the flavor.)

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt oleo; add cocoa and milk.	Bring to a boil and add sugar and vanilla.

title: banana crush
directions: Put bananas, orange juice and lemon juice in blender.
Add other ingredients and freeze.
Thaw for 3 hours and serve.

title: bran spice muffins
directions: Mix bran and milk; let sit 10 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix liquid ingredients together, then add to dry mixture.
Add bran mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12.

title: six week muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a huge bowl; mix well by hand. Combine all the wet ingredients. Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix well.
Store in a wide-mouth gallon jar in refrigerator.
The batter will keep for 6 weeks if you haven't consumed it by then.
When desired, fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until they test done.

title: gitmo cheese balls
directions: Cream together cheese and butter.
Add salt, flour and paprika; mix well.
Drain olives.
Wrap 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture around each olive and place on cookie sheet.
Place cookie sheet in freezer.
After balls are frozen, place in plastic bag and store in freezer until ready to use.
Take quantity needed out of freezer and place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs together.
Add eggs last, one at a time (mixing after each egg).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes (in Bundt pan).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the following ingredients together:
zucchini, eggs, vanilla, liquid oil and sugar.
Then add:
soda, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nuts, if desired.
Slowly add flour, a little at a time.
Mix together and pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onion slightly in butter.
Add rest of ingredients in large kettle and simmer slowly 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: banana breakfast bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy (high speed).
On medium speed, beat in egg, salt, cinnamon and bananas. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into greased pan. Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into 12 bars.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in oven in shallow roasting pan (15 x 10 x 2-inch).
Remove.
Mix in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereals, nuts and pretzels.
Mix thoroughly to coat all pieces.
Return to oven for one hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Pour out on absorbent paper to cool.
Remove excess oil.
Store in airtight container.

title: texas red chili
directions: Braise meat and
onion	until
well done.
Mix in Texas Red Chili seasoning, flour
and
cups au jus or beef stock. Simmer mixture for approximately 20 minutes, stirring often so chili does not
stick	and
burn.
Serve
in
bowl topped with grated cheese and
diced onions. Serve with taco salad, nachos and burritos.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Butter crackers and crumble to make 1 cup.
Cook broccoli in microwave.
Set aside.
Place crackers in bottom of casserole.
In microwave, saute onion, 2 minutes.
Add mayonnaise, soup and eggs to make a sauce.
Pour into broccoli and blend.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle more crumbled crackers on top.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes on High power or until mixture is set.
Cover with cheese and microwave until melted.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix softened cream cheese; add milk and Worcestershire sauce. Mix together; add crabmeat with spoon, then add onion.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: two-cheese fettuccine primavera
directions: Cook fettuccine as directed on package.
Meanwhile, combine onion, garlic, Butter Buds or chicken broth, basil, oregano and black pepper in a 2-quart glass measure.
Cover with venter plastic wrap and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir flour into onion mixture.
Using wire whisk in a salad bowl, blend milk into mixture; recover.
Stirring with whisk after every 2 minutes, microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes or until thickened.
Stir Mozzarella cheese into mixture and set aside.
Place broccoli and bell pepper in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain pasta and stir reserved sauce into it along with vegetables.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and serve immediately.

title: homemade caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°. In 2-quart pan combine brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture comes to a full boil, 12 to 14 minutes.
Continue stirring until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Stir in baking soda.
Place popcorn in grocery bag.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Shake. Place popcorn on jelly roll pan.
Spread out. Bake 20 minutes. Stir.
Continue baking for 25 minutes more. Remove from oven immediately.
Place caramel corn on waxed paper. Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: peanut butter fudge(no cook)
directions: Mix well.
If you want chocolate, add 3 tablespoons cocoa. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into pieces.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain.
Return to pan; add cream of mushroom soup, corn, salt and pepper.
Simmer while making mashed potatoes.
In a 2 x 9 x 13-inch baking pan (glass or aluminum), pour ground beef mixture in pan.
Layer with mashed potatoes; top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon, crumble and set aside.
In bacon grease, saute bell pepper, onion and celery until soft.
Drain and mix with butter beans and soup.
Heat until hot.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: cranberry citrus warmer
directions: In large saucepan or pot, combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Over medium heat, simmer about 15 minutes to blend flavors.
Remove spices with a spoon.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Heat through.
Serve hot.
Garnish as desired.

title: mexican enchiladas
directions: Mix meat, soups, enchilada sauce, onion and spices.
Layer in a large baking dish with tortillas or chips.
Cover with cheese. Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: party nuts
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add the mixed nuts.
Remove nuts from egg whites.
Put sugar in plastic bag.
Put nuts in bag of sugar and shake until all coated.
Put in large ungreased cookie sheet in 1 even layer.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until crispy, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together first 6 items.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool, then serve.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Arrange in shallow, 2-quart casserole; use glass.
Combine all other ingredients to make sauce.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 300° (uncovered) for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings (at least).

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados to desired texture.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Chill.
(Green onion, green bell finely chopped, garlic, lime juice, salt and pepper, and cumin can all be added if desired.)

title: fresh cranberry relish
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine juice, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add cranberries and raisins.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes or until cranberries pop. Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans.
Transfer to a serving bowl. Cover and chill thoroughly until serving time.
Makes 8 (1/3-cup) servings.

title: nancy nicholas cookies
directions: Cream the butter well.
Add sugar and salt.
Cream thoroughly. Add flour and blend in completely.
Shape dough into 2 rolls approximately 1 to 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap individually in wax paper and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Cut and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
(They do not spread.)
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: williamsburg spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and let cool.
Mix all ingredients together in the order given, except tomatoes. Arrange tomato slices on greased cookie sheet and place scoop of spinach on top of each slice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Spinach mixture can be made the day before and refrigerated.

title: baked round steak
directions: Wash round steak under cold water to remove any bone residue left from slicing.
Place steak flat in 8 1/2 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Place onion slices over steak.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Do not uncover until done.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream shortening (add sugar gradually) until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat until smooth. Stir in mincemeat.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet (two inches apart).
Bake at 400° about 12 minutes.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: nina's baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a pan and add milk and flour (as needed) to make a medium thick white sauce.
Do not let the white sauce turn brown.
Add salt and pepper and cheese, saving some cheese for the topping.
Let cheese melt into the cream sauce.
Pour the white sauce over the cooked macaroni and top with the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbling and almost brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Soak whole cabbage for 10 minutes in cold water; cut in 1/2-inch strips.
Put in boiling water; boil for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and let set for 5 minutes; drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese and cream of mushroom soup in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Put layer of cabbage and top with mixture, another layer of cabbage and rest of mixture.
Top with bread crumbs; heat in oven.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add pineapple.
Top with bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake in buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off fat.
Cook and grind chicken and pork.
Use broth from pork and chicken as needed to cook.

title: chestnut hors d'oeuvres
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: spinach squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
