Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven. Beat eggs; add flour, milk, salt and baking powder, then add cheese and spinach.
Be sure spinach has been squeezed dry.
Mix well.
Pour in pan and bake for 35 minutes.
Cool and let set. Cut into squares.

title: key lime cake
directions: Beat the cake mix, pudding mix, water, oil, lime juice and eggs, just until ingredients are blended and no large lumps remain. Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan; bake for 55 minutes at 350°, or until cake is done.
Cool cake in pan until lukewarm.
Poke holes into cake with large fork.
Blend together the topping ingredients thoroughly.
Pour topping over cake.
When cake has cooled completely, turn out onto a serving platter and pour any topping from baking pan over the cake.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, vanilla and sugars; add egg and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Sift in chocolate and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderately hot 350° oven about 12 minutes.

title: bacon green beans
directions: Saute onions and fry bacon.
Set bacon aside.
Cook green beans and onions.
Add seasonings to taste.
Add bacon.
Leave approximately 2 to 3 tablespoons of bacon grease in pan so beans don't stick and to flavor.
Do not overcook beans.
Leave a little crunchy but done.

title: caramel corn
directions: Keep popped corn warm in a very low oven while making the syrup.

title: awesome carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, pineapple (drained), vanilla and carrots.
Sift the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in very lightly greased 9 x 15-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with Awesome Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: deviled ham turnovers
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add shortening and rub very lightly with tips of fingers.
Add milk and roll out 1 or 2-inches thick.
Cut in 4-inch squares.
Brush with butter and put in 1 teaspoon of deviled ham in 3 corners square shape.
Brush over with butter and bake in moderate oven.
Makes a good lunch or snack.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Cream the
butter,
sugar and vanilla. Sift and stir in flour and
salt.	Mix
in
nuts. Chill dough. Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until set, but not brown. While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: sour cream cinnamon rolls
directions: Let yeast and warm water rise about 10 minutes.
Stir in 2 1/4 cups warm sour cream, sugar, soda, salt, eggs, shortening, then flour to make soft dough.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick. Cover with melted butter, then cover with cinnamon and sugar. (Add raisins now if wanted.) Roll and cut 1/2-inch thick.
Place on pans; let rise.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Cut ribs and place in shallow pan.
Sprinkle on salt, pepper and onion.
Roast uncovered at 450° until browned, about 20 minutes.

Combine all other ingredients, except lemon slices; bring to boil over medium-high heat, then remove from heat. Remove meat from oven, top with lemon slices and pour on sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with milk.
Mix with all other ingredients except nuts and place in an 8-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Good with Fritos corn chips.

title: easy peanut butter tasty-cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake according to box instructions in a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan, 11 x 17-inch.
Baking time should be on box (usually 25 minutes).
When cake is done and still hot, spread peanut butter on top.
(Peanut butter will melt and spread easily.)
Cool cake until peanut butter sets.
Frost cake with the chocolate icing.

title: asparagus-almond casserole
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk, salt and pepper and cook.
Add cheese, stirring continually until blended.

Line a 1 quart casserole with a layer of asparagus, almonds, then sauce. Continue until all ingredients are used, topping with almonds. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly, approximately 20 minutes.

title: peppermint tea concentrate
directions: Bring 2 quarts water to a boil.
Pour
over tea leaves. Steep 15 minutes with lid on.
Strain over
sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Boil 1 quart water.
Steep same
leaves
more minutes.
Mix with sugar solution, 1 quart concentrate to 3 to 4 quarts water.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a medium bowl and mix well.
Stir in vegetable oil.
Add buttermilk and stir until blended.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries; stir until strawberries are thawed.
Pour into oblong dish; refrigerate until firm.
Combine nuts, pineapple and whipped topping.
Spread over firm gelatin.
Refrigerate until top layer is firm.
Cut into squares; serve on lettuce leaf.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine milk, oil and egg white in cereal until moistened. Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to cereal mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Bake in muffin pans at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 small muffins.

title: company creamed spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, stir and top with cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand in a large bowl.
Pour into cake pan and bake at 325°
for 45 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Dust with powdered sugar and cinnamon.

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve with cut up fruit.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Blend in eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture. Add apples and nuts; mix thoroughly. Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Use whip cream for frosting.

title: bun bars
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, peanut butter and butterscotch chips.
Spread half of mixture on greased jelly roll pan.
Boil 1 minute, vanilla pudding and milk and 2 pounds of powdered sugar. Spread on top of chocolate layer.
Chill.
Mix 1 pound dry roasted peanuts with other half of chocolate mixture.
Put on top of pudding.
Chill thoroughly and cut.
May freeze.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and pecans in blender.
Pour sugar over the blend.
Prepare jello with hot water and undiluted orange juice.
When jello is syrupy, stir in cranberry mixture.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients (except brown sugar) together in large pan. Whiz other ingredients in blender.
Add liquid to dry ingredients. Mix thoroughly.
Put in large shallow pans and bake at 250°.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes to prevent burning.
Bake until golden brown and crisp, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with milk.
Add fruit, if desired:
fresh peaches, strawberries or fruit puree.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients in an 8-inch cake pan. Then make 3 wells in the mixture.
Put vanilla in first, vinegar in the second and margarine in the third.
Pour water over all and mix with a fork until ingredients are entirely mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling salted water 8-10 minutes, drain. Wash with cold water, drain. Add remaining ingredients except cheese. Add a small amount of butter on top of casserole. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Remove from oven, sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook ground beef and onions in large pot until brown; drain. Add garlic salt, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and undrained mushrooms.
Mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni shells and drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Pour 1/2 of the shells in a large, deep casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 of the sauce.
Spread 1/2 of the sour cream over the sauce and sprinkle 1 package of the Mozzarella cheese over the sour cream.
Repeat layers.
Cover; continue baking until cheese melts and browns slightly.

title: little chicken dinners
directions: Shape sausage into 1-inch balls.
In medium skillet, brown balls.
Remove and drain.
Pour fat from skillet.
Melt butter over low heat; stir in flour and salt until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth, cream and mushrooms with liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Heat oven to 425°.
Divide chicken, sausage and sauce into 6 ungreased individual baking dishes.
Place one pastry round on each dish, fold pastry under, even with edge of dish.
Flute.
Cut slits on top.
Place dishes on baking sheet and cover with aluminum foil. Remove foil the last 10 minutes of baking.
Bake 30 minutes or until crust is brown.
Insert pastry chicken in each baking dish. Makes 6 servings.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice in bowl.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine ground beef, eggs, salt and pepper in bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into miniature meatballs.
Add to mixture in pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer.
Transfer to chafing dish. Serve hot with wooden picks.
Yield:
40 servings.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Select good ripe figs.
Mash well.
Add sugar.
Cook over low heat about 20 minutes or until color changes.
Add Jell-O directly from package.
Cook another 10 minutes while still hot.
Put into jars and seal.

title: chili and rice
directions: Brown hamburger in a big pot.
Pour off excess grease.
Add onion and green pepper; brown.
Add beans and tomato sauce.
Add water.
Sprinkle in chili powder; blend in.
Simmer about 30 minutes and serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: apple crisp(microwave)
directions: Put apples in 8-inch square microproof baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and crumble over top of apples.
Cover with waxed paper.

title: molasses-peppermint soda
directions: Mix in glass the molasses and milk.
Add 1 scoop of ice cream. Fill glass with soda.
Stir with the candy peppermint.

title: schaum torte
directions: Mix together sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat egg whites.
Add sugar mixture gradually and continue beating until mixture will hold its weight.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into spring-form pan and bake in slow oven (275° to 300°) for 50 minutes.

title: pecan delight
directions: Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Melt one box semi-sweet chocolate with 2-inch square of paraffin wax.
Roll candy in chocolate and place on wax paper until hard.

title: homestyle pork (beef) stew
directions: In casserole dish, combine all ingredients, except flour.
Mix flour and water; sprinkle over mixture.
Cover casserole.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours until meat and vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain cherries.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in top of double boiler.

title: icebox dessert
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add beaten egg yolks and pineapple.
Line pan with crushed vanilla wafers.
Alternate layers.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Wrap each dog in a crescent triangle. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Serve with ketchup. Makes 10 servings.

title: simple and delicious fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in an oblong casserole dish in oven.
Meanwhile, mix flour, sugar and milk in a bowl with a whisk.
Pour flour mixture on top of melted margarine.
Spoon in pie filling on top of flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serve warm.
Can be served with ice cream, whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: nutty italian
directions: In an 8 ounce coffee glass, put Amaretto and Frangelico.
Fill with hot cocoa, whipped cream and cinnamon stick for garnish.

title: cornbread sticks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Spray cornbread or muffin tins with cooking spray.
Place in oven for 5 minutes to heat while preparing batter.
In a medium size bowl, combine flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and cornmeal.
Set aside.
Place egg whites in a 2-cup glass measure; add milk to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Stir in applesauce.
Pour egg white mixture, all at one time, into flour mixture.
Stir until all dry ingredients are moistened.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Beat milk and eggs. Toss with cooked spaghetti.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with Ragu sauce.
Arrange sausage or pepperoni slices over sauce. Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix in peanut butter and sugar.
Gradually add milk and mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate overnight. Garnish with peanuts.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and sugar; beat until stiff.
Fold in crushed soda crackers.
Add 3/4 cup nuts and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Spread in a greased dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cover with Cool Whip.
Top with 1 can cherry pie filling.

title: tallerinia
directions: Brown meat; add onion, green pepper, tomato paste, olives, corn, salt and garlic salt.
Add noodles; put in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: aloha spread
directions: Combine and form in ball.
Chill slightly.
Can roll in pecans, if desired.

title: jeffy salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over pineapple.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Add other ingredients.
Mix all together and serve.

title: springtime vegetable slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, broccoli, tomatoes, celery and cucumber in large salad bowl.
Whisk together remaining ingredients for dressing.
Pour over vegetables; toss to coat well.
Yield:
10 servings.
Contains 87 calories per serving.

title: linguini with asparagus and chicken
directions: Cut up chicken in 1-inch cubes.
Chop onion finely.
With fork, mash clove of garlic into paste until smooth.
Trim off tough asparagus ends.
Peel stalks, if desired (the little points on stem, optional).
Cut in diagonal 1-inch pieces.
In heavy skillet, saute chicken in olive oil 5 minutes or until no longer pink. Remove from skillet.
Add onion and garlic paste.
Cook until onion is tender (softened), but not brown.
Stir in chicken broth and asparagus.
Cook 2 minutes or until just crisp.
Add and heat whipped cream until very hot (do not boil or let curdle).

title: sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water. Add remaining ingredients. Knead for 5 to 10 minutes. Let rise 2 times. Make into buns or rolls. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the white sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Count the minutes once it starts to boil.
Mix the peanut butter and marshmallow; stir well.
Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Add sugar and water mixture with peanut butter and marshmallow.
Pour in the pan.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased casserole dish. Top with 1 cup bread crumbs tossed with 1 tablespoon butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Spread bread with butter.
Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage; drain well.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt; mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover and chill overnight. Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: microwave caramel nut cream pie
directions: Blend butter, sugar, spices and salt.
Beat egg yolks and add. Sift in baking powder and flour, then add the water and honey. Put figs and raisins through food chopper and add.
Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys (1st clause of Proverbs 23:14).
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: yam biscuits
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain, remove skins and mash. Beat shortening into hot yams until blended.
Cool.
In a separate bowl, sift dry ingredients together.
Add to yams and work together until well blended.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured 2-inch cutter.
Place slightly apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
(Bottoms will be very dark, but will not taste scorched.)

title: bavarian bake
directions: Mix potatoes and kraut.
Add soup and salad dressing.
Top with sausage or hot dogs or whatever.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham loaf
directions: Pour milk over bread crumbs.
Combine with other ingredients and mix well.
Form loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese chicken livers
directions: Marinate overnight.
Drain, spread on cookie sheet and sprinkle with flour from a sieve.
Sprinkle generously with dark brown sugar.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes.
Turn.

title: rice salad
directions: In a medium saucepan combine water, rice and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for about 12 to 24 hours.
The longer it cooks the better the taste.

title: peanut butter roll candy
directions: Mix confectioners sugar with milk until it can easily be rolled on a flat surface sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Spread with peanut butter and roll up tightly in jelly roll style. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Cut in slices to serve.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Take off tip of spoon or roll into balls.
Make dent in top and fill with apricot, raspberry or any kind of jam.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put in basket of coffee maker, sugar, allspice and cinnamon. Run liquids (apple cider, cranberry juice, orange juice and sugar) through Mr. Coffee with dry ingredients in basket with filter or use percolator.
Serve hot.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant; slice about 1/2 inch thick.
Dip in beaten egg and milk mixture and roll in bread crumbs.
Place in hot oil and cook until all sides are golden brown.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package (yellow rice). Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add to rice the remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sugar free strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan combine cornstarch with small amount of water until well blended.
Add remainder of water, bring to a boil, stirring until clear, remove from heat.
Add jello and blend until smooth. Cool slightly, then add strawberries.
Pour mixture into pie crust and chill until set, can be topped with low calorie whipped topping.
(Other fruit and corresponding jello can be substituted.)

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook 3 hours on low heat.

title: london broil
directions: Mix together Accent, salt, sugar, onion, dry mustard, rosemary, ginger and peppercorn.
Add lemon juice; mix well.
Add salad oil and garlic.
Place steak in a glass dish and add marinade. Marinate in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours (or overnight), turning meat occasionally.
Remove meat from marinade and place on broiler rack. Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 5 minutes on each side.
Cut steak in thin diagonal slices.
If meat in 1 1/2 inches thick, it may take 7 to 8 minutes per side.
Check by cutting into center. Don't cook too done or will be tough.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls from cans.
Spread each whole sheet flat onto jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: russian tea cakes(makes 4 dozen cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
Cool, then roll in more powdered sugar.
Yummy!

title: $250.00 cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars together. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix together in separate bowl the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Slowly add dry ingredients to cream mixture. Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts. Roll into balls about 1 1/2-inch in diameter. Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Heat all ingredients.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put raw pieces of chicken on top.
Salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 more minutes.

title: sesame broccoli
directions: In a small pan, cook sesame seed over medium heat for 3 minutes, shaking pan occasionally; set aside.
Cut broccoli into florets; peel stalks and diagonally slice.
Boil broccoli for 5 to 6 minutes or steam until tender-crisp; drain and place in serving dish.
Combine orange juice, sesame oil, soy sauce and ginger root; toss with broccoli.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a large Dutch oven. Drain excess fat. Add water, tomatoes, potatoes, garlic, salt and pepper.
Boil on medium heat until potatoes are done. Add macaroni when potatoes are almost done. Continue cooking until macaroni is tender.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach following directions on package.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Shape into small balls (1 1/2-inch round).
Place on a cookie sheet.
Freeze, then later bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
This batch yields 60 balls.
Can be made ahead.
Put in a plastic bag after freezing and put in freezer until ready to cook and serve.

title: breakfast fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You can add nuts or coconut if desired.

title: cheese bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour and 1 package active dry yeast.
Heat 1 1/2 cups shredded American or Swiss cheese, 1 1/4 cups water, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring constantly.
Add to flour mixture; add 1 egg.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in as much of 2 to 2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour as you can mix in with a spoon.

title: jack daniels' intoxicated chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
In a large skillet, heat butter; brown chicken on both sides.
Add Jack Daniels whiskey; ignite whiskey, if desired.
(Igniting the whiskey lessens the flavor of the whiskey.)
When the flames go out, add the onion.
Cook for one or two minutes.
Add thyme, parsley and water.
Cover the skillet and cook over a low heat, turning occasionally, 25 to 35 minutes.
Transfer chicken to a warm platter.

title: beaver stew(adapted from:  l. l. bean and go hog stew)
directions: *Season flour with black pepper, salt, savory, rosemary and thyme, then add flour mix to stew.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add eggs with a fork; lightly beat eggs into pumpkin mixture.
Add the evaporated milk and milk; mix well.
Place a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate on oven rack; pour in pumpkin mixture.
Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil; bake for 25 to 30 minutes more or until a knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Cool. Cover and chill to store.
Serves 8.

title: beef soup
directions: Brown beef in water in large pan.
Put seasonings and let simmer for about 2 to 3 hours, then cut up meat and put vegetables in and simmer 1 hour and eat.

title: salmon cakes
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Cover and refrigerate 10 minutes or until slightly firm. Shape mixture into 4 patties about 3/4 inch thick. Spray 12 inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Heat over medium high heat until hot. Add patties; cook 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown, turning once. If desired, serve with additional nonfat sour cream.

title: white frosting
directions: Part One:
Cook until thick flour and milk.
Cool completely.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel apples and core.
Cut up and microwave for 5 minutes, covered.
Before cooking, sprinkle on Sweet 'N Low and cinnamon.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit; great with apples.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice.
Mix in Cool Whip and add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Dressing:
Prepare dressing the night before and refrigerate until you're ready to serve. Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, 2 Top Ramen chicken flavor packages (silver packages), salt and pepper.

title: "death by chocolate" trifle
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, prick with fork and pour Kahlua over cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken-stuffing bake
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan over high heat, heat 3/4 cup of milk and butter to scalding.
In large bowl, pour hot milk mixture over stuffing; toss to mix well.
Pat half of the stuffing into buttered 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl, stir soup, remaining milk, chicken, 1 cup cheese, celery, broccoli and thyme until well mixed.
Spoon evenly over stuffing mixture in baking dish; top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pie glaze
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until clear (about 1 minute after it comes to a boil).
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly firm.
Pour over strawberries in baked pie shell.

title: stacy's chicken salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise,
lemon juice and lemon pepper. Toss this with chicken chunks, celery and grapes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix wet ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix dry ingredients in a separate bowl and then add to wet ingredients. Mix until combined.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: french apple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched and pulls away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Top with sugar glaze.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and let cool.
(Add soda.) Cream shortening and sugar. Sift flour (save 1/4 cup to dredge nuts).
Add salt and cereal to flour.
Beat eggs and add milk. Add sugar and shortening mixture to milk and egg mixture.
Add water and raisins.
Add dry ingredients and blend until moistened. Fold in nuts.
Place in a tightly covered container. Store in refrigerator.
This makes 4-quarts.
Batch will keep 6 weeks. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Blend together the sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar.
Layer your salad container with all ingredients; top with dressing, cheese and crumbled fried bacon.
This salad tastes even better when made the day before serving.

title: peanut patty
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, water and peanuts together.
Boil hard for 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla, salt and food coloring.
Beat until creamy.
Pour out on buttered cookie sheet.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water and boil 5 minutes.
Add beets, cover pan and let stand 1/2 hour.
Just before serving, place back on heat and bring to boil.
Remove and add butter.

title: grandma mills sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix in heavy saucepan or iron skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Very delicious.

title: lean beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Place meat and vegetables in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Add tomato juice.
Cover with foil, sealing edges tightly.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: hot chili-cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips.
Heat, stirring occasionally, over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve heated as a dip with chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: diabetic milk shake
directions: Put frozen milk in blender.
Pour milk, sweetener and flavoring in blender.
Put blender on medium speed until mixed well.
Make sure all the ice milk is chopped up.
It has only about 75 calories per blenderful and very little fat.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Brown and drain well the ground chuck.
Add chopped onion and celery (or celery salt).
Put tomato sauce and paste in with ground chuck; mix well.

title: easy prune cake with sauce
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, cloves in a large mixer bowl; mix well.
Add oil, eggs, prunes and beat well.
Stir in pecans. Pour into a greased, floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until done.
Drizzle with Prune Cake Sauce.

title: mini fruitcakes
directions: Line 18 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups with paper liners.
In large bowl,
combine
egg, water and extract.
Stir in mincemeat.
Add quick bread mix, nuts and mixed fruit.
Stir until dry
particles are moistened, about 50 strokes by hand.
Fill prepared muffin cups
full.
Place
a	cherry	in center. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove
from
pan.	Cool
on rack before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; pare and slice potatoes into pressure pot. Add water and salt. Bring pressure up and turn off heat. Let pressure go down and drain potatoes. Put into 2 quart casserole dish; set aside.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vanilla, butter, cinnamon and egg.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add bread cubes and raisins. Mix.
Pour into well-buttered baking dish; set in pan of warm water.
Bake in 350°
oven about 1 hour, or until inserted knife comes out clean.
May be served with whipped cream or other topping.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Combine water, cocoa and margarine in a pan; bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar. Stir.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: maui onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter slowly until soft and golden brown. Stir in flour to form paste.
Add bourbon and stir until smooth. Gradually add beef bouillon and basil; simmer for 40 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix garlic and butter spread on French bread.
Toast on cookie sheet in oven.
Ladle soup into ovenproof bowls.
Top with bread sprinkled with cheese.
Broil until golden and bubbly.

title: butterhorns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, beaten eggs and melted shortening (not too hot).
Mix in flour and refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough in 2 parts and mix in a little more flour (enough to roll out).
Roll each part in a circle and cut in wedges.
Brush each with butter and roll in a horn.
Place on a cookie sheet and let rise 3 to 4 hours.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place in buttered casserole dish; layer with cheese.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over broccoli and cheese mixture.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sauerkraut and dumplings
directions: Layer pork chops or pork meat with sauerkraut in a pressure cooker, Dutch oven or in an ovenproof casserole.

Add 2 cups water and bake or cook until pork is so tender, it breaks apart when prodded with a fork (in pressure cooker, about 20 to 25 minutes). Remove sauerkraut and meat pieces to a bowl with a slotted spoon. Just slightly thicken the liquid in the pot and season with salt, pepper or beef bouillon as needed.
Mix liquid into sauerkraut to make a nice moist casserole consistency.
Add the dumplings and then serve with applesauce on the side.

title: centennial turkey chowder
directions: After meat has been removed, break up turkey carcass from cooker or raw turkey and put in large kettle. Cover with 2 quarts of water and bring to a boil.
Cover kettle.
Reduce heat slightly and continue to boil gently for about 2 hours.
Strain broth and measure.
There should be 7 to 8 cups.
Add water if necessary. Remove any bits of meat from the bones, cool and dice.
Add to any diced or chopped leftover turkey.
Try to have at least 1 cup of meat, but preferably 2 cups.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of sugar, flour, egg yolks and milk in double boiler.
Put the other 1/2 cup of sugar in pan and brown, then pour the browned sugar in the double boiler and add flavoring and butter with a cup of pecans, if you like.

title: cheese balls
directions: Put in blender all ingredients.
Put nuts in cheese, then roll on the outside.

title: chrissy's favorite salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Dissolve Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups hot water and add pinch of salt.
Add 1/2 cup juice from fruit.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add to Jell-O and juice mixture.
Add nuts and stir.

title: superior beef hash
directions: Take scraps of beef and chop fine.
Spread cold, mashed potatoes over the bottom of your dish.
Over the top of that, add the chopped meat, a little butter and a little pepper and salt. Bake and eat hot.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix Veg-All, soup, sour cream and cheese right in the dish.
Mix melted margarine with crushed cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over all.
May add more cheese on top if you like. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time (have eggs at room temperature).
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add sour cream. Add vanilla and coconut.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mrs. porto's tiramisu
directions: Separate the eggs.
Beat the egg yolks and sugar together into a smooth consistency.
Add the cheese and fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add liquor to Espresso.
Soak the ladyfingers in the coffee (do not leave too long or ladyfingers will be soggy).
Line the bottom of an oblong pan with half the ladyfingers and spread over half the cream mixture.
Cover with remaining ladyfingers and the rest of the cream mixture.
Cover top with cocoa powder.
Chill until served, preferably overnight.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar.
(Save less than half of mixture for topping.)
Spread remainder into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chop and potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoning salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.

title: mexican ribbon cake
directions: Divide the layers into half, making 4 layers.
Mix the chocolate pudding with 2 cups cream and whip.
Mix the vanilla pudding with 2 cups cream and whip until thick.
Alternate the cake layers with cream, ending with a white cake on top and top with chocolate cream.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach and tear into bite size pieces. Wash and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Combine Jell-O with boiling water. Fold in strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts. Turn half of the mixture into an 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan and chill until firm (about 1 1/2 hours).
Leave remaining mixture out of refrigerator.
When half is firm, spread evenly with sour cream and top with remaining Jell-O mixture.
Chill.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
In medium bowl, mix 3 1/2 cups flour with other dry ingredients; cut in Crisco.
Stir in buttermilk, yeast mixture and egg; blend thoroughly.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead slightly, adding remaining flour, if needed.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch cutter, dipping into flour as needed.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Let dough rise slightly.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: sweet-sour pickles
directions: Empty
pickles	into
a large pan.
Keep liquid and add sugar. Cut pickles into slices and put back into jars.
Cover with liquid
and
seal.	Turn
jar back and forth to dissolve remaining sugar.
Let set a day or so.

title: pa's molasses cookies
directions: Combine oil
and
cup
sugar in a large mixing bowl. Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses; combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and ginger.
Add to molasses mixture, stirring to mix. Roll dough into 1-inch balls;
roll each in remaining 1/4 cup sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350°
for
10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yield:
About 4 dozen.

title: instant ice cream tarts
directions: Mix together the coconut and butter and line 8 (5 ounce) custard cups; refrigerate.
When ready to serve, fill cups with ice cream.
Top with any of the following: crushed pineapple, strawberries, chocolate or butterscotch sauce, chopped nuts, apricot or raspberry jam.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot banana bread
directions: In bowl, combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; gradually add to creamed mixture, alternating with bananas.
Stir in carrots and pecans. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack to cool completely.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Cut carrots into 1/4-inch slices and boil in salted water until tender.
Drain and cool.
Alternate layers of carrots, pepper and onion in a large bowl. Make marinade of remaining ingredients, beating until completely blended.
Pour over carrots and refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10. It is best when allowed to season several days before serving.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: cajun marinade
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend to a paste.
Cover meat, brisket or any other variety and wrap in foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Can cook on grill or in oven at 375° until done.

title: slaw
directions: Mix and put in mold to set.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt and stir together the margarine and flour.
Set aside. Cook remaining ingredients, except chicken, until tender.
Add chicken and flour mixture; cook until thick.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with biscuit crust and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden.

title: luscious cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together graham cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix in margarine thoroughly.
Press mixture evenly in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes. Cool.
Reduce oven to 300°.
Beat cream cheese in large mixing bowl.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add lemon peel and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake 1 hour or until center is firm.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender, but not mushy.
Drain.
Cut onion into rings.
Cut green pepper into rings, discarding seeds. Combine onion and green pepper with carrots in heatproof bowl.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening until the mixture resembles corn meal.
Add liquid ingredients.
Chill and roll out. No matter how much the crust is handled, it comes out flaky. Bake single crusts at 425° for about 10 minutes.
Follow recipe directions when doing double crust pies.
Using a circle of foil around the edge of these for a few minutes during baking helps avoid overbaking the edges of the pies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook corn syrup and brown sugar.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add pecans, butter and vanilla and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Place pecan halves on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Cut wing tips off and cut in half.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Place chicken in large shallow pan and cover with marinade for at least 1 hour (or overnight).
Bake uncovered on cookie sheet at 350° for 45 minutes until tender and brown.
Turn once.

title: tahini dressing
directions: Put ingredients into a blender.
Blend until well blended.

title: coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Mix in milk and coconut.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: ooey gooey butter cake
directions: Mix melted butter and 1 egg with cake mix.
Press into bottom of a buttered cake pan.
Beat powdered sugar, cream cheese and 3 eggs together.
Pour over cake mixture and bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: cream of broccoli
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Sir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk; stir constantly.
Bring to a boil. Add broth and broccoli.
Cook over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes, until tenderness of broccoli is to taste.
Stir occasionally. Don't boil.

title: cream puff heart
directions: Fold a 9 x 8 1/2-inch sheet of paper in half lengthwise. Sketch half of a heart on it; cut out.
Open paper to full heart; trace with grease pencil on baking sheet.
Grease sheet slightly. Heat water and butter in saucepan to boiling; reduce heat.
Add flour; stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth after each addition.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls, with sides touching, along edge of heart outline on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes; cool on rack. Cut off top.
Fill shell with Cream Filling; top with strawberry. Replace top.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 8 servings.

title: yum yum gingerbread
directions: Blend molasses, sugar, shortening and egg in electric mixer, about 2 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients and add gradually.
Add boiling water last.
It makes a thin batter.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
It makes very light gingerbread that doesn't get dry.

title: cheese dreams
directions: Have butter and grated cheese at room temperature.
Blend. Add milk, unbeaten egg white and salt.
Mix well until creamy. Chill.
Remove crusts from bread and cut into 1 to 2-inch cubes. Ice 5 sides with cheese mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Keep cool until ready to bake.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: buttermilk spice cake
directions: Sift together into a mixing bowl the flour, 1 1/2 cups of sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Cool the melted butter and stir into flour mixture along with buttermilk.
Mix vigorously until batter is very smooth.
Grease 10-inch tube cake pan and dust lightly with granulated sugar. Pour in batter.
Bake in preheated 325° to 350° oven for about 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool on cake rack for 15 minutes, then unmold.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring the brown sugar, margarine, Karo and salt to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add soda; stir until foamy.
Place corn in a brown paper bag (sprayed with Pam); shake well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on level 9.
Enjoy.

title: heavenly chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave sugar and Karo syrup on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and microwave on High 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Take out of microwave and add soda. Pour onto flat buttered pan.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and caraway seed.
Cut butter into flour until crumbly.
Add beaten eggs to dry mixture.
Mix in raisins, currants and buttermilk and stir into a soft dough.
With floured hands, knead dough lightly and quickly into a ball.
Shape dough into approximately a seven-inch round and place in a nine-inch pie tin.
Cut a deep cross with a floured knife into the dough, marking it into quarters, called "farls".
(This helps with the rising, divides the bread easily and according to tradition, brings a blessing on the baking.)
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for about one hour.
You may test for doneness by tapping your hand on the bottom of the loaf; if the sound is hollow, the bread is ready.
You may also test by inserting a skewer, which when removed dry, indicates doneness.
Let the bread stand almost an hour before serving.

title: chili verde
directions: Fry your pork in a very small amount of oil until well done. Remove the pork from the grease and add about 1/4 cup water to the grease.
Add soup, chilies, jalapeno and garlic salt. Simmer all ingredients until well blended, about 45 minutes.
You may add more or less water for your desired thickness.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Put first 8 ingredients into large mixing bowl; mix until blended yet lumpy as in muffin mixture look.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.
Heat in pan 1/2 cup cocoa, butter, add powdered sugar; mix well and pour on cake.
Top with nuts.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread dessert topping on bottom of crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pat 2/3 of dough in a greased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Spread pie filling over dough in pan.
Crumble remaining dough over pie filling.
Bake about 30 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Separate the rolls and place on the bottom of a 13-inch cake pan.
Bake as directed on package.
Cream together the mayonnaise, cream cheese, dill weed, garlic powder and dressing mix.
Spread this on top of the cooled crescent rolls.
Mix the tomatoes, celery, lettuce, onion and pepper and press on top of the last layer.
Top everything with Cheddar cheese.
Cut and serve.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with vanilla and salt until soft peaks form. Slowly add sugar, beating until stiff, not dry.
Fold in coconut. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: enchilatos
directions: Brown meat with pepper and onion; season to taste.
Heat chili with a little water to blend.
Roll meat inside tortillas and place side by side in baking dish.
Pour chili on top and spread cheese over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: "mama's coconut skillet balls"
directions: Combine sugar, dates and eggs in a large skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring continuously until mixture pulls away from sides of pan (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and nuts.
Carefully stir in cereal.
Cool slightly.
Moisten hands in cold water and shape mixture into rolls or balls.
Roll in coconut flakes.
Chill and store in container in refrigerator. Makes about 2 dozen, according to size.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Add all other ingredients and heat thoroughly until cheese is melted and blended.

title: oven barbecue
directions: Cover brisket with first 4 ingredients.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator in well covered pan.
In the morning, salt and pepper and pour generous amount of Worcestershire sauce.
Roast 5 hours at 275°.
Uncover, pour 1 cup barbecue sauce and bake 1 more hour.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine Raisin Bran, sugar, flour and soda in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix only until blended (do not overmix). Store, covered, in refrigerator (4 to 6 weeks).
Fill muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: paprika redskins
directions: Arrange potatoes in a 2-quart microwave-safe dish, skin side down; cover.
Cook on High 8 to 10 minutes, or until almost done. Rotate after 4 minutes of cooking.
In a 1-cup glass measure, melt margarine or butter on High 30 to 45 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Pour over potatoes; stir to coat and cover. Cook on High 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, or until done.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: skinny soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook slowly in a covered pan.
Cook for 1 to 1/2 hours.
May season more or less to taste.
Low in calories.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix
flour, sugar and baking powder together with milk. Then melt
butter
in
pan
you bake in.
Add flour mixture in drops all over butter (do not stir).
Add hot peaches all over the mixture
(do
not
stir).
Bake
about 45 minutes in 350° oven. Good with vanilla ice cream.

title: apple-cheddar muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 9 ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Stir to combine and set aside.
In blender, combine remaining ingredients and process until smooth.
Pour into dry ingredients and stir until moistened (do not beat or overmix). Prepare muffin pan.
Fill each cup with an equal amount of batter (each will be about 3/4 full).
Bake in middle of center oven rack for 20 minutes.
Cool and serve.
Great for breakfast or as part of a light lunch.
Makes 12 servings.

title: jalapeno quiche
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, Tabasco sauce, jalapeno peppers and garlic salt.
Grate cheeses and place in butter greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares while warm.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix together. Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Thaw Cool Whip; add Jell-O and pineapple.
Stir until well mixed.
Chill and serve.

title: half cup cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and oil.
Beat in egg.
Mix flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to butter mixture.
Add rest of items.
Roll in small balls.
Press flat with fork on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 or more minutes.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cocoa for a crowd
directions: In a large kettle, combine sugar, cocoa, salt and warm water; mix well.
Add boiling water; boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in hot milk.
Serves 100.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine eggs, corns, muffin mix, sour cream and margarine. Spread in an 11 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mac-nut toffee
directions: Butter an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place half the nuts in the pan. Sprinkle half of the grated chocolate over the nuts.
Combine butter and sugar in a heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture is the color of peanut butter (about 290°).
Remove from heat and immediately pour over chocolate in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate and then nuts.
Press nuts firmly into chocolate.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: grandma's cheesecake
directions: Melt margarine and add to the cracker crumbs.
Press mixture firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.
Mix lemon jello into 1 cup boiling water.
Drain pineapple and add to jello. Set aside to cool.
Beat chilled Pet milk with sugar.
Slowly add cream cheese and jello, beating together until well mixed.
Pour into pan with crust mixture. Chill at least 3 to 4 hours.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush cookies; add margarine.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (for crust).
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Chill 20 minutes.
Prepare pudding with 2 1/4 cups milk.
Spread over mixture.
Chill.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over filling.
Top with cookie crumbs.
Let chill 8 hours or overnight.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat all together the sugar, molasses, shortening and eggs until creamy.
Add water.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add last.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Ovens may vary.

title: peanut butter power bars
directions: Stir together oats, dates, raisins, flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, beat peanut butter, margarine, eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients to this and stir with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Press in a greased (lightly) 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in lard.
Add milk all at once. Knead lightly; roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out and place on greased baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Brush top with melted butter.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Heat to rolling boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil for 1 minute without stirring.
Place pan of frosting in bowl of ice and water.
Beat frosting until smooth and of spreading consistency.
Stir in vanilla.
Frosts two 8 or 9-inch layer pans or 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: bread pudding
directions: Arrange bread sections in oblong dish; mix remaining ingred ients and pour over bread and bake in 350° oven approx. 30 m inutes until slightly browned.

title: coco not cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar, butter and coconut extract. Add egg and blend well.
Stir in Bix-Mix and spud flakes.
Blend well.
Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Put all ingredients in blender except for 1 tablespoon lemon juice and the oil.
Start blending and add in slow steady stream the oil until mixture is thickened.
Slowly add 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Beat well.
Chill before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cranberry bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl stir together the flour, oats, brown sugar, orange peel and baking soda.
Stir in the melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Reserve one cup of the flour mixture for the topping.
Pat the remaining mixture into the bottom of an ungreased 8 x 12-inch rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Carefully spread the cranberry sauce over the baked crust.
Stir the chopped nuts into the reserved topping mixture. Sprinkle it on top of the cranberry sauce.
Lightly pat it into the sauce.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes more.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into bars.

title: cheese soup
directions: In heavy pan, melt oleo. Add veggies and saute (covered) over low heat until tender. Do not burn. Add 1/2 cup flour. Stir in gradually. Add chicken broth. Cook and stir until thickened slightly. Add milk gradually and bring to simmer. Add soda and cheese. DO NOT BOIL. Cook awhile stirring until cheese melts.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces.
Dry with paper towel and sprinkle Accent and pepper on both sides.
Open cream of celery soup and put about 1/2 can of soup in bottom of Pyrex dish and then put in chicken pieces.
Pour remainder of soup on top of chicken pieces.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: brown sugar glazed sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange potatoes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Combine sugar, butter, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and ginger in heavy small saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over potatoes; toss to coat.
Cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake potatoes 50 minutes. Uncover; bake until potatoes are tender and syrup thickens slightly, basting occasionally, about 20 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to 500°.
Top potatoes with marshmallows and nuts. Return to oven; bake until marshmallows begin to melt and nuts begin to brown, about 3 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish (large).
Layer potatoes, carrots, onion and ground beef.
Pour both soups over; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Add sugar and let stand for 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and combine well.
Refrigerate.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix together.
Pour into well-greased and floured pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Fill 2/3 full and sprinkle on topping.

title: brown derby pot roast
directions: Tie clod to hold shape while cooking.
Rub with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in heavy roaster.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Add more oil, if needed.
Add diced vegetables and saute until golden.
Sprinkle flour onto vegetables.
Mix well and continue cooking about 4 to 5 minutes.

title: oven cinnamon french toast
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Dip 6 slices of bread.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 500° for 5 minutes on each side or until toasted.

title: #1 venison marinade
directions: Add ingredients together in sequence, as listed, in large bowl.
Stir well; pour over venison and allow to marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.
This marinade may be used on venison that is to be barbecued or roasted in oven.

title: carrot ring
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until they stand in soft, stiff peaks.
Fold egg whites into carrot mixture.
Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes.
Turn onto serving plate.
Fill center with cooled peas and onions, or any other desired vegetable.
Makes 8 servings.

title: deedee's chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Use solid shortening to grease 9 x 13 pan.
Combine first 4 ingredients by hand.
Pour into pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
tags: Betty Crocker chocolate fudge cake mix

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Add chopped onions and green pepper. Saute a few minutes, stirring with the meat. Add tomato sauce and catsup.
Cook about 35 minutes.
Add kidney beans.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4 or more.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Add mushroom soup, chicken soup, shrimp and tomatoes.
Heat and serve over cooked rice.

title: frosty creme de menthe
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients except mints.
Blend on high speed 1 minute or until smooth.
Serve in champagne glasses. Top each with a mint triangle.
Makes ten 1/2 cup servings.

title: festival chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Brown in oil.
Add onion and garlic; cook lightly.
Stir in tomato sauce, sherry, water, bouillon cubes, chili powder and salt.
Cover tightly; simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with olives and mushrooms.
Serves 6.

title: creamy egg and noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles; drain and put in a bowl.
Melt butter in a small skillet; saute onion and garlic until tender.
Toss noodles with onion mixture.
Chop 6 eggs; save 2 for garnish.
Add to noodle mixture.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in a small bowl. Then fold into noodle mixture.
Turn into a baking dish.

title: luscious coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, making 2 (8-inch) layers.
When completely cool, split both layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Blend well and chill.
Reserve 1 cup coconut mixture.
Spread remainder between layers.
Combine reserved mixture with whipped topping; blend until smooth and spread on sides and top of cake.
Seal in airtight container and refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: no-bake cheesecake(blueberry, strawberry or cherry)
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust. Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with pie filling before serving.
Keep refrigerated. Enjoy!

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: In at least an 11-inch iron skillet, melt butter and brown sugar.
Cook and stir over medium heat until the mixture bubbles. Remove the skillet from burner.
Smooth out the brown sugar mixture.
Arrange the pineapple rings over the brown sugar mixture in the skillet.
Place a maraschino cherry in the center of each ring.
Carefully and evenly spread the crushed pineapple over the pineapple rings.
Mix boxed cake mix according to the box directions using real butter.
Pour the batter over the pineapple and bake in a pre-heated 350 oven for about 1 hour.
Check for doneness in the center of the cake using a toothpick.
Cool the cake in the skillet 20 minutes before inverting it onto a large plate.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: swedish cabbage pudding(meat loaf)
directions: Chop cabbage coarsely and saute in butter or margarine.
Add Karo syrup and vinegar.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix hamburg, bread, pepper, salt, onion powder, allspice, nutmeg, egg and catsup.
Mix well.
Grease baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with one-half of the cabbage mixture.
Spread hamburg mixture over the cabbage and then put the rest of the cabbage and juice on top of the hamburg.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix it all together; dip chicken before and during grilling.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with Triscuits, vegetable dippers or baked pita.

title: easy cobbler sugar-free
directions: Melt the oleo in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a bowl mix all ingredients. Pour in the pan with the oleo.
Pour 1 quart of fruit over this.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Melt oleo; stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips last.
Batter will be stiff and thick.
Spread on a large, slightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Mix room temperature cheese with softened margarine.
Add sifted flour and pepper.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Take small pieces of dough and roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; add into a large bowl.
Add all the ingredients; mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: bean and beef soup(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Put 16 bean soup in crock-pot; let set overnight (8 to 10 hours) in water two times as much as that of beans.
Brown beef on stove in Worcestershire sauce and lemon pepper, salt and pepper to taste.
Put bouillon cube, onion and cooked meat in crock-pot with beans.
Cook 4 to 6 hours on high; reduce to low and cook for 6 hours.

title: chili dip
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, heat on High all ingredients until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Serve warm with assorted vegetable dippers or tortilla chips.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients and add peach juice.
Pour in baking dish over melted butter.
Drop peach pieces over top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt effie's cranberry cheese dip
directions: Put cranberries through food chopper using finest cutter. Blend cheese and horseradish until smooth.
Whip in cranberries and sugar.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with whole-wheat or stone ground crackers.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll out crescent rolls; spread butter over top and sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over top.
Spread pecan pieces over top. Roll up in log shape; cut into slices and bake in greased cake pan at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole for two
directions: Place wild rice and white rice in medium saucepan. Add 1 cup water. Bring to a boil.
Cover, leaving slight gap in lid so it won't boil over.
Turn burner to warm and let cook 20 to 25 minutes or until just dry.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham crackers with oleo.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 3/4 crumb mixture.
Let jello set until syrupy.
Add soft cream cheese and jello mixture.
Put on top of crumb mix in pan.
Add the rest of crumbs on top.
Put in freezer.
Take out a few minutes before you want to serve.
Rich!

title: lenny's pancakes with sausage
directions: Cook sausage; save some sausage grease to mix in the pancake batter.
Mix pancake mix, egg, milk and oil in bowl.
Add cinnamon, vanilla extract and sausage grease.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Let frozen potatoes thaw.
Meanwhile, chop onion and saute in butter.
Mix soup, sour cream, salt, pepper, onion and Cheddar cheese together.
Add potatoes to mixture.	Place in 3-quart casserole.	Melt butter and mix with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham biscuit with sauce
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat.
Now slice whole package of rolls and lay top off to side.
(I use electric knife.)
Spread sauce over bottom half of rolls.
Place ham or beef on top of sauce and then sprinkle cheese on meat. Place top of rolls.
Freeze or bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed, except ginger ale. Freeze.
Thaw approximately 5 hours before serving time.
Pour 1 quart ginger ale over punch mixture; stir well.
Serves 50.

title: "potion"
directions: Take several small boys and girls

title: quiche zucchini pie
directions: Mix altogether and bake in buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown and set.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Chill dough.
Shape into a small ball. Dip in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: country rib barbecue
directions: Boil ribs until tender.
Flake meat with a fork, removing fat and bones.
Mix barbecue sauce and water in a cup.
Pour mixture over flaked meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns with a dash of Texas Pete.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 2 cups boiling water.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients except ginger ale.
Add this just before serving.
Serves 50 people.

title: five in one
directions: Layer bacon on bottom of cast-iron skillet.
Make hamburger into one big patty and place over bacon.
Slice onion and potatoes over hamburger.
Put peas over top.
Cook 1 hour over low heat until hamburger and potatoes are done.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Stir 1/2 c. sugar into fruit and set aside. Melt butter in baking pan. Sift flour and sugar together. Add milk a little at a time and mix well until smooth. Pour batter into pan of melted butter. (Do not mix), then pour berries over batter. Bake for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter snowballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients until they form a ball.
If too crumbly, add honey.
Chill 1 1/2 hours.
Roll balls and cover with coconut.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook broccoli until tender, drain well. Stir and add soup and sour cream.
add remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti and meat balls from la casa cafazza
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll meat balls into size of golf balls. Brown in a small amount of olive oil.
Cook in spaghetti sauce.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Heat chocolate and hot water over low heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat whipping cream in 1 1/2-quart bowl until stiff.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spoon into pie shell.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Garnish with fresh fruit, whipped cream, chopped nuts or grated chocolate, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: granny's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Drain off grease while still hot.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In skillet, stir sugar, flour and cocoa until lumps are out. Add hot water to dissolve dry ingredients.
Then add Milnot. Bring to a boil.
Stir in vanilla.
Boil until gravy becomes thick.
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: 7-cup salad
directions: Pour hot water into the lime Jell-O.
Stir until it is thoroughly mixed and all Jell-O is melted.
Add the sugar.
Add the 7-Up soda.
Stir again.
Next, add the crushed pineapple, the cream cheese and the nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into a Jell-O mold or loaf pan.
Put in the refrigerator and chill until set.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: garlic bundt loaf
directions: Cut or snip off pieces of the dough about the size of a walnut. Place half in a greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Combine the melted butter with rest of the ingredients.
Pour half of this butter mixture over dough in pan.
Add the remaining dough pieces and drizzle the rest of the butter mix over the top.
Cover and let rise until double in size, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes before removing.
Bread can be eaten by breaking off pieces or by slicing.

title: shrimp and clam dip
directions: Mix together and serve with chips.

title: spinach salad
directions: Finely chop the egg white and
serve for garnish.

title: strawberry-rhubarb puff
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In an ungreased baking pan, mix rhubarb, strawberries and 1/2 cup sugar; place in oven.
Measure flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Pour oil and milk into measuring cup (do not stir together).
Pour all at once into flour mixture.
Stir until mixture cleans side of bowl and forms a ball.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Whip cream cheese at medium speed.
Add milk gradually.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat in pudding slowly.
Fill pie shell. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: golden brown chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in sour cream mixture, then dredge in stuffing mix.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Drizzle with butter and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine chocolate, evaporated milk and butter in saucepan. Over low heat, cook mixture until smooth.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and add sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and pecans; mix well. Add this mix to cooked mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Filling should be firm.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown onions and beef in butter.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into casserole dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Add a little butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix hot water and jello until jello dissolves.
Add can pineapple.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until they melt.
Put in refrigerator until cool and set. Then add whipped cream, pecans and cottage cheese to mixture. Stir well and jell about 2 hours.
Serves about 12.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: In bowl, add the vegetable oil, sugar, egg, mashed bananas and almond extract. Beat well. Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon and mix into batter. Stir in the crushed pineapple and chopped almonds. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: refreshing jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package instructions.
Let semi-gel for about 2 hours.
In bowl, gradually add Cool Whip to jello, beating with electric mixer until nice and pink.
Pour mixture into 9X13 Pyrex dish.
Return to refrigerator and chill until firm.
Top with remaining Cool Whip before serving.

title: baking pan "greaser"
directions: Mix equal parts of Crisco and flour until all the flour is absorbed into the Crisco.
Store in closed container and keep in the refrigerator.
Keeps very well.

title: fancy chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in roasting pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375° in oven or cook in slow cooker for 8 to 10 hours on low heat.

title: frozen yum-yum dessert
directions: Mix together graham crackers and butter.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan (all but 1 cup).
Mix together ice cream, pudding and milk.
Spread on top of graham cracker crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top of ice cream mixture.
Sprinkle the remaining one cup of graham crackers on top.
Freezer for approximately 2 to 4 hours to harden the ice cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mushroom, peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange half of asparagus in a buttered 6 cup casserole.
In a bowl, mix gently the peas, soup and cheese.
Spoon half the mixture into casserole.
Add remaining asparagus, and top with remaining peas.
Toss the crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until crumbs are golden brown.

title: mushroom gravy
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion, mushrooms and parsley in 1/4 cup broth until vegetables are tender. Combine cornstarch, pepper and 1/2 cup of broth. Stir until smooth. Add to pan with the remaining broth. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Boil for 2 minutes. Yield: 2 cups.

title: deep fried vegetables
directions: Combine ingredients.
Dip vegetables in mixture.
Deep-fry until golden brown.
Any fresh vegetable will do.

title: italian macaroni pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch pie pan or 9-inch square pan.
Prepare macaroni according to package.
Drain.
In a large skillet, brown beef with celery and drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni, eggs, cheese and garlic.
Toss lightly.
Place in prepared pan.
Press evenly in bottom and up sides, forming a crust.
Pour meat mixture over macaroni crust.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove foil.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add water and bananas; thoroughly mix in flour, soda and nuts.
Cook at 325° until done, approximately 70 minutes.

title: jean's mexican corn bread
directions: Brown ground beef in saute pan.
Pour off fat.
About 3 minutes before turning off heat, toss in and stir the onions and cayenne pepper.
Add salt.
Mix together in bowl, corn meal, corn, eggs and milk.
Pour into well-greased iron skillet or bread pan. (Do not pour excess oil into corn bread mix.)
Pour 1/2 the mixture into pan.
Spoon beef mixture over corn bread.
Gently pour in rest of corn meal mix.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, then increase temperature to 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Bake to golden/crusty brown.
Serve with Tamales Ole Grande or just plain old greens and beans.

title: apple torte
directions: Mix apples and nuts in a large mixing bowl.
Combine dry ingredients and add to apple-nut mixture.
Combine beaten egg, vanilla and melted butter; pour over dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Batter will be very stiff.
Spread in greased 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or hard sauce.

title: lite no bake lemon cheesecake
directions: Finely chop graham crackers. Mix with margarine.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of 9-inch springform pan.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Bring 1 cup of water and 1/2 teaspoon salt to a boil.
Add rice; cover and simmer until tender, about 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, drain and rinse peas.
Slice green onions.
In a large frying pan, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble bacon.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Put the cooked rice, peas, green onions, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper into the pan and heat through, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in bacon and serve.

title: open-faced crab sandwiches
directions: Combine crabmeat and lemon juice; toss gently. Add green pepper and next 5 ingredients. Stir well. Spread about 1/2 cup crabmeat mixture on bread of your choice.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Garnish with lemon slices, if desired, and serve immediately.

Yields 4 servings. Contains 113 calories, 11.1 grams protein, 5.9 grams fat, 3.5 grams carbohydrate, 65 milligrams cholesterol, 257 milligrams sodium and 62 milligrams calcium per 1/2 cup crabmeat mixture.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Measure dry ingredients together and set aside.
Mix together sugar, eggs, oil, pineapple, zucchini and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well and pour into 2 loaf pans (greased).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa thoroughly.
Add beaten egg yolks and a little of the milk.
Mix well.
Cook, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens.
Add butter and vanilla and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: grandma's frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Mix eggs, sugar and flour in saucepan.
Bring juices to boil and pour over egg mixture.
Add softened gelatin and marshmallows.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until thick.
Cool.
Add fruit and whipped cream and mix well.
Pecans may be added.
Freeze overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 12.

title: fruit jar bread
directions: *Two cups sweet potatoes or zucchini squash may be substituted for pumpkin.

title: chicken and dried beef
directions: Put a layer of diced beef on the bottom of a casserole dish. Put a layer of chicken.
Put bread on top.
Next, beef layer.
Mix and cover chicken with mushroom soup, carrots and 3 pieces of shredded beef.
Bake at 300°, uncovered, for 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: bright sunday morning meal
directions: For a Sunday morning treat, serve the above on a tray with a red rose to your loved one.

title: chicken and wild rice salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Combine rice, chicken, water chestnuts, green onions, celery, nuts and grapes in a bowl with tight fitting cover.
Add enough dressing to moisten. Refrigerate 1 to 2 days before serving.

title: summer blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water and two cups blueberries.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add butter, then rest of blueberries.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
(Can also substitute strawberries or peaches.)

title: orange cooler dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Add sherbet and stir until melted.
Pour into mold and chill until thick and syrupy.
Stir in oranges.
Chill until firm.
Serve with whipped topping.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: green beans mandarin
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage and clams in saffron sauce
directions: Scrub and clean clams.
Wash and cut leeks and celery.
Cook leeks and celery in water or water and Clamato juice until limp. Add saffron and clam juice.
Let simmer until browned.

title: jolderndon's onion rice
directions: Stir ingredients into oven-safe cookware.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir before serving.

title: top of stove casserole
directions: Mix and brown meat and onions.
