Cook macaroni separately; add to meat mixture.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Heat together and serve.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in bacon drippings until tender. Add meat and rice.
Mix well.
Add eggs.
Cook, stirring until eggs are set.
Add soy sauce.
Heat through.

title: spiced beets
directions: Cook beets until partly done, peel and slice.
Put into pickle mixture and simmer a few minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: chicken broth (for soup base)
directions: Cut chicken in pieces; put all pieces except breast in kettle with cold water.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Cover and bring to a boil; simmer 15 minutes, then skim off scum that rises to surface.
Add breast pieces; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Strain and use cooked chicken as desired.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts broth.

title: chicken and stuffing strata
directions: Sprinkle 1 cup stuffing mix in a buttered 8-inch square pan. Sprinkle chicken, celery and onions over that.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.

title: corn and ham bake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the eggs.
Mix in all but butter and bell peppers.
Saute bell peppers in butter.
Add to first mixture.
Butter a 7 x 11-inch casserole dish; turn mixture into dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Toss gently.
Top with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, reserving 1 cup of pecans for rolling ball in.
Form ball and roll in 1 cup of pecans.
Chill.

title: wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine oil, salt, sugar and dry milk; dissolve with yeast.
Stir in wheat flour.
Stir in white flour, adding the last cup a little at a time by kneading it into the dough.
Let dough rise in bowl until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Divide dough in 2 parts.
Form loaves in greased bread pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: cherry torte
directions: Crush crackers; add melted butter and sugar.
Put in baking dish or pie pan; press firmly.
Beat soft cream cheese with mixer. Add 1/2 cup sugar gradually.
Then add eggs and beat at high speed until smooth.
Pour over cracker crust.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove and cool.
When cool, add pie filling.
Chill 3 hours or overnight.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Mix with celery soup, mayonnaise and onion.
Put in casserole.
Top with crackers and cheese.
Drizzle melted oleo over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Blend into Cool Whip.
Add other ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Serve at once, but it's better to let it set awhile until marshmallows soften a bit.

title: savory party mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour margarine over combined ingredients.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir twice while baking.

title: cherry almond dessert
directions: Combine pie filling, cinnamon and almond extract.
Spread in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over the filling.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix and sprinkle nuts. Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: noodle chicken bake
directions: Add 1 tablespoon salt to rapidly boiling water.
Gradually add noodles so that water continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Drain.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and save juice from pineapple.
Drain and save juice from apricots.
Add enough apricot juice to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Add lemon juice to other juices.
Mix this juice with pudding mix.
Mix apricots and pineapple into pudding mixture. Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Just before serving, add sliced bananas and nuts; mix well.

title: rancher's stew
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion. Drain grease. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Parboil the potatoes. Cut into chunks. Add to hamburger in pan. Add kidney beans and cans of soup (undiluted). Mix all together. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serve with cornbread.

title: rich dark carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan after mixing all together.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add chopped or instant onion.
Stir in undiluted soup and mushrooms; add sour cream and serve over rice with a green vegetable on side.

title: orange-nut bread
directions: Place juice from orange in measuring cup and fill with boiling water.
Force orange rind and raisins or pitted dates through coarse blade of food chopper.
Add diluted orange juice. Stir in shortening, vanilla and egg.
Add flour, sifted with salt, baking powder, soda and sugar.
Beat well and stir in nut meats. Bake in greased 1 pound loaf pan in moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour.
Cool in pan before slicing.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add carrot.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: an actress' artichoke dip
directions: Start with enough mayonnaise to equal the desired quantity of dip.
Add ingredients to taste.
Mix and refrigerate for several hours before serving for best flavor.
Serve with hot or cold cooked artichokes.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Combine all ingredients. Pour into 1-qt. casserole.
Sprinkle 1/4 c.
cracker crumbs on top and drizzle 1 Tbsp. melted butter over crumbs.

title: italian turnover
directions: Combine onion, garlic, salt, oregano, pepper and heavy cream. Add spaghetti and toss thoroughly.
Place 1/2 mixture in 10-inch frying pan.

Arrange salami on top, then 1/2 slices of Provolone. Top with remaining spaghetti mixture, then remaining cheese. Cover and cook over medium-low heat 25 to 30 minutes until bottom is a crusty golden brown.
Invert into serving plate.
Garnish with additional salami, pimento-stuffed olives and parsley as desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Dissolve brown sugar, butter and granulated sugar with milk. Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water (234° to 240° on candy thermometer).
Add cornstarch, dissolved in a little cold water.
Stir in.
Take immediately from the stove and beat well. Add vanilla and peanut butter.

title: *baked lamb with orzo
directions: Brown lamb chops in roasting pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt, pepper and oregano. Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: fruit cake(moist)
directions: Boil sugar, cold water, raisins, Wesson oil, apples, salt, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and cocoa together for 4 minutes.
Cool and mix well with flour, soda, walnuts and fruit cake mix.
This freezes well.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cool and pour over mixed vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight. Keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Allow to sit in refrigerator to stiffen (rolls easier). Roll into balls.
Place on a cookie sheet or pan. Bake for about 20 minutes at 300°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients with a mixer, then sift the dry ingredients into mixture.
Add the vanilla last.
Mix well and spoon out small amounts of dough and roll into balls.
Lay them out on a cookie sheet and press them with a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add ingredients in order.
Place in greased 9 x 5 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan at once and cool on wire rack.

title: spirited cranberry punch
directions: In punch bowl, combine cranberry juice, pineapple juice and ReaLemon brand.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and liqueur. Serve over ice.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Put pineapple and cherries into cake pan. Prepare cake mix according to the instructions on the box. Pour the cake mixture over the pineapple and cherries.
Pour melted oleo over the top of cake mix. Add coconuts and nuts. Bake at 350°.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, onion soup mix, eggs and bread crumbs.
Shape into small balls.
Place balls in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Drain; place in dish.
Mix barbecue sauce, honey and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Makes 36 balls.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add beaten eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Work in the oats and nutmeats.
Roll and chill.
Slice and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: pink fluff pie(yield: 9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Lightly grease and sugar bottom of sides of pan with cookie slices overlapping slightly to form a scalloped edge (use about 1/2 roll). Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown; cool.

title: mint sauce
directions: Put mint leaves on a chopping board with sugar.
Chop with a sharp knife (the sugar not only enhances the flavor of the mint, but makes chopping the leaves easier).

title: coconut tube cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and stir in flavoring and coconut.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan.
Start in a cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: molded blue cheese spread
directions: Pour wine into blender container.
Sprinkle with gelatin.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes to soften.
Add hot milk, whirl for 2 minutes or until gelatin is dissolved and blended.
Add Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Add cheeses, a few cubes at a time, whirling until mixture is smooth and well combined.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: First layer:
Combine the pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and melted margarine and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: humdingers(recipe originated from louise pippin)
directions: Simmer butter, sugar and dates over low heat for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add other ingredients.
Cool; roll into small balls.
Drop into bag containing powdered sugar and shake well. Set balls on platter or cookie sheet to dry.
Should make 50 balls.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend together peanut butter and cream cheese, then add Cool Whip to peanut butter mixture.
Pour in graham cracker crust. Store in refrigerator 3 or 4 hours before serving.

title: baked french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until limp and buttery.
Mix in undiluted beef broth, wine, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt. Heat through.

title: **springerle cookies
directions: Stir sugar and eggs for 1/2 hour. Then add flour.
Roll out not quite 1/2 inch.
Put impression on.
Let lay overnight.
Bake in slow oven until done.

title: johnnycake(cornbread)
directions: Cut 1/2 cup soft butter or margarine into dry mixture.
Add 3 eggs and beat.
Add 1 cup milk and beat in.
Pour in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine all ingredients until all zucchini is coated.
Pour in 1/2 deep in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crush punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and freeze.
When ready to serve, set out of freezer for 1 1/2 hours.
Chop up and pour ginger ale over. Makes a slushy punch.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Mix 1/3 to 1/2 cup of mixture to one cup of boiling water.

title: pull apart ring
directions: Prepare Whole Wheat Not So Sweet Dough.
On a lightly floured surface, roll 1/4 of the dough into a rectangle measuring 8 x 16-inches.
Cut into squares measuring 4 x 4 inches.

title: really great chicken
directions: Saute onion and butter until soft.
Add soup, mushrooms and wine or water.
Blend well.
Place chicken in casserole dish and spoon sauce over.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Serve sauce on the side.
Good over rice.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In separate bowl mix pudding (dry), milk, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Mix with 1st mixture. Crush 1 small pkg. Oreo cookies in blender.
Layer in bowl, ending with the cookies.
Put in childs sand pail with shovel or a flowerpot and plastic flowers.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans, cover with water, adding 1 tablespoon salt, and soak for at least 3 hours or overnight.
Put beans in 2 quarts of water and let boil slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add precooked sausage or ham.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 30 minutes more.
Serve in a bowl over rice.

title: three month slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 2 hours. Squeeze dry by handfuls.
Put in large bowl with celery and peppers (chopped).

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and salt until clear.
Remove from heat and add jello and a little red food coloring.
Let cool; slice in one quart of strawberries (after being washed!) into cooled liquid.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and make small balls (walnut size).
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Turn and bake 10 more minutes. Mix the remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Heat and add meat balls.
Simmer 1 hour or so.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine the blackberries, 1 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and lemon extract.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, nutmeg and remaining sugar and salt.
Add milk; stir just until mixed.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into six mounds onto hot blackberry mixture; cover tightly and simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: double chocolate mocha trifle
directions: Lightly spray 9 x 13 baking dish and bake brownies according to "cake-like" directions. Cool completely. In a large bowl, whisk pudding into milk until thickens.

title: waffles
directions: Beat ingredients with wire whisk or hand beater until well blended.
Pour onto center of hot waffle iron.
Bake until steaming stops.
Remove carefully.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased loaf pan. Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.
This makes a lot.

title: grilled tri-tip roast
directions: Whisk first 10 ingredients in medium bowl.
Using small sharp knife, pierce meat all over.
Place meat in large resealable plastic bag; add marinade.
Seal bag.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight, turning plastic bag occasionally.

title: clark gable's favorite coconut squares
directions: Mix 1 cup of flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup of butter thoroughly;
press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: party chiffon cake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Mix together the oil, egg yolks, cold water and vanilla.
Beat the egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff and then fold into the first mixtures.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes and then increase oven to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Bake in tube pan.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer.
Can add 1 medium pepper.

title: peanut-chocolate dessert
directions: Cut margarine into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal; stir 2/3 cup peanuts into flour mixture.
Press peanut mixture into a 13x9x2 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool completely.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Combine cooked noodles with tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion, green pepper, pimento and peas.
Blend soup and milk.
Add cheese.
Stir and add to noodle mixture.
Turn into 2 quart casserole dish. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on high for 5 minutes. Remove and stir again.
Sprinkle paprika and almonds on top. Cover and cook on high for another 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Arrange half of the bread in bottom of a greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over bread and top with ham.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper, mustard, onion and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl.
Pour mixture over bread slices. Cover with foil. Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes and mash.
Add other ingredients.
Pour mixture into buttered large casserole dish.
Dab with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 1/3 cup of water.
Wash and hull berries.
Select 1 cup of poorest berries.

Add these to sugar and 1 cup of water; bring to a slow boil and boil 15 to 20 minutes. Strain boiled mix through wire sieve, crushing berries with spoon. After juice is squeezed from berries, return juice to pan. Discard berry pulp.
Place juice over medium heat.
Stirring constantly, add cornstarch.
Simmer slowly until thick.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add remaining berries to baked pie shell. Cover with sauce.
Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Cream together cream cheese, onion, Bac*Os and milk.
Cut crust off bread.	Roll bread flat and spread a coat of creamed mixture on each slice of bread.
Allow 2 spears per slice and place corner to corner on bread.
Roll up.	Use toothpick to hold together if needed.
Brush melted butter across top and bake 20 minutes or until brown at 400°.
Then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Beat next 3 ingredients and spread on cooled pretzel crust.
Chill.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
When jello is slightly thickened, add strawberries.
Let set again until slightly thickened.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and saute onions.
Combine with chili powder.
Reserve one cup of cheese.
Spoon enough meat mixture and cheese on each tortilla to cover a third of it.
Roll tortilla, beginning at the filled edge.

title: frozen fruit drink
directions: Mix and freeze juice, lemonade and cream of coconut. When ready to serve, put scoop of mixture in a glass. Add 7-Up to child's drink, brandy for adults.

title: braised beef round steak(campfire cooking)
directions: You will need a Dutch oven.

title: beef with wheat
directions: Wash meat, pat dry.
Cover with water and bring to a boil. Cook 10 mins., discard water.
Add fresh water and boil meat until tender.
Shred meat, put back in water, add beef broth if needed for flavor.
Wash wheat, add to beef
with spices. Stir until wheat is cooked.
1-2 tbsp. of margarine or butter gives extra flavor.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and cornstarch. Beat egg yolks and Pet milk. Stir until creamy. Add whole milk. Cook over low heat, stirring until thick. Add vanilla and coconut.

title: sweet and sour pork stir-fry
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Brown in butter.
Remove from pan.
Put onion and pepper in.
Cook until tender.
Add steak back in then add 1 bottle of sweet and sour sauce.

title: hungarian almonds
directions: In large bowl beat egg whites until frothy.
Mix in paprika, garlic salt and cayenne pepper; blend thoroughly.
Add almonds; toss to coat evenly.
Spread in single layer on lightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake in 300° oven 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally until lightly toasted.
Loosen from pan and cool. Stor in airtight container.
Makes 2 cups.
Very good for the holidays.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to hard ball stage, stirring constantly.
(Test in cold water.)
Stir in dates and pecans.
Roll in damp towel, chill and slice.

title: chunky chicken rice soup
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large saucepan until browned.
Add broth, water, vegetables, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in rice and parsley; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the French fried onions and paprika.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Cover with French fried onions and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: stuffed celery(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix ingredients together well and stuff celery pieces.
Makes 6 servings.
One stalk equals 1/2 meat and 1 vegetable.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat well.
Dissolve soda in 3 tablespoons milk; add to creamed mixture.
Add flour and juice to cream mixture, blending well. Mix 1 cup flour well with raisins and nuts.
Pour batter over floured nuts and raisins; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat together egg whites, powdered sugar and oleo for 5 minutes.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Cut the bananas lengthwise and lay on top of egg mixture.
Drain the pineapple and place on top of bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with nuts, cherries and chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate before eating.

title: lamb and cabbage(far-i-kal)
directions: Cut cabbage into serving wedges and layer with meat in a heavy casserole.
Sprinkle each layer with a little salt and flour. Place cheesecloth bags of peppercorns on two opposite sides of casserole.
Pour boiling water over meat and cabbage and bring to a boil.
Skim off fat.
Cover and let simmer on low heat until meat and cabbage are tender, shaking pot often, 2 to 3 hours. Serve with boiled potatoes, pickled beets and flat bread.

title: pear or apple butter
directions: Cook 1 1/2 hours, stirring constantly to keep from sticking. Place in jars and seal.
Can cook less time if thick enough.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Melt
butter
in
saucepan.
Add bread crumbs.	Combine all ingredients together in blender.
Mix on high speed until mixture is	smooth.
Top oysters with 1 tablespoon of mixture and broil for
and
minutes or until lightly browned or oysters are thoroughly heated.

title: cauliflower broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook frozen veggies as directed; drain.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter; stir in flour and seasonings until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Sprinkle onion, pimiento and cheese over vegetables. Pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sarah parton's barbecue sauce
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer a few minutes.

title: indian sweet and sour chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in a wide skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook, turning, until golden on all sides.
Remove and set aside.
Add remaining oil to drippings, along with garlic and onions.
Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring until golden.
Stir in sugar and spices. Cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Stir in vinegar and broth.
Add chicken; cover, reduce heat and simmer until meat is cooked through.
Season with salt and taste.
Sprinkle with seeds.
Serve over rice, with plain yogurt on side.

title: scripture cake
directions: Bake in moderate oven until done.

title: portland bouillabaisse
directions: Saute the chopped celery, onion and green pepper in the butter. Use large kettle.
Mix the flour, curry powder, powdered cloves, brown sugar, salt and pepper together until lumps disappear and then add to the kettle; stir in.
Then add the Tabasco sauce, tomato juice, sherry or lemon juice.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Reduce heat and add seafood and parsley.
Serve. Serves 4.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: ham and swiss melt
directions: Slice rolls in half.
Lay the top half aside.
Layer cheese and ham.
Replace tops.
Melt butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Divide butter mixture in half and drizzle over the top of each pan of rolls.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.

title: sara's wedding punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Add Jell-O.
Let cool.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Mix well and freeze.
Thaw for 3 to 4 hours.
Place in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Serves 25 to 30 people.

title: artichoke torte
directions: Blend cream cheese and dressing mix.
In a separate bowl, stir together artichokes, peppers and parsley.
In a 3 cup bowl, lined with plastic wrap, alternate 4 layers of cheese and artichoke mixtures (makes 2 layers) beginning and ending with cheese mixture.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Invert on plate before serving, remove plastic wrap and serve with crackers.
Makes a very pretty appetizer!

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Drain maraschino cherries.
Make fondant by mixing thoroughly the softened margarine, Karo and powdered sugar.
Cover each cherry with about 1 teaspoon fondant.
Put on cookie sheet.
Cool fondant balls in freezer, but do not let the cherries freeze.
In double boiler, melt together the paraffin, chocolate chips and Baker's chocolate.
Keep warm.
Remove cherries from freezer and dip into chocolate sauce.
Put on wax paper to harden.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Mix soup with milk.
Cook noodles and peas.
Mix noodles, peas, soup mixture and tuna in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: louisiana red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans in water.
Season with salt and bacon drippings, ham or other seasoning meat.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add onion, garlic, celery and bay leaf.
Continue to cook over low heat for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Whip together first 4 ingredients.
Place wafers in bottom of cupcake papers.
Fill 3/4 full with whipped mix.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with pie filling and store in refrigerator.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Chop and mix all vegetables.
Put into large kettle to cook. Cover with V-8 juice and enough water to cover.
Bring to boil; simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to 310° or hard crack stage.
Add butter, vanilla and peanuts.
Cook until amber color and add soda and beat well.
Spread as thin as possible with buttered knives. When cool, loosen and break into pieces.
Secret to successful brittle is to work very fast to spread thin.

title: delicious punch
directions: Mix jello with hot water to dissolve.
Add cold water, sugar, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Pour into a large container and freeze.
About 30 minutes before serving, remove from freezer. Pour frozen mixture into punch bowl.
Add large bottles of ginger ale to mix and stir.

title: shrimp, cauliflower and snow pea salad
directions: Make dressing.
Halve shrimp horizontally and cook in 6 quarts boiling water with 3 tablespoons Crab Boil for 30 seconds or until they turn pink.
Drain the shrimp; transfer them to a bowl and toss with 1/4 cup of the dressing while still warm.
Chill the mixture, covered, for 1 hour.
Trim the cauliflower and separate into flowerets.
Cut the flowerets into smaller pieces, leaving 1-inch of the stem attached.
In a large saucepan of boiling salted water, blanch the cauliflower for 1 minute; drain in colander and refresh under cold water.
Transfer the cauliflower to a bowl; toss while still warm with 1/4 cup dressing and chill the mixture for one hour.
Break off ends and remove strings from snow peas and blanch in boiling water for one minute.
Drain in colander and refresh under cold running water.
Toss with 2 tablespoons of dressing and chill the mixture, covered, for 1 hour.
Trim and discard the coarse stems from watercress and in a large bowl, toss with shrimp, cauliflower and snow peas.
Transfer salad to a large serving bowl and drizzle the remaining dressing over it.

title: lime custard
directions: In a small saucepan, stir 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and gelatin until well blended.
Stir in water.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Pour half the hot sugar mixture into the eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Pour egg mixture into remaining hot sugar mixture; stir until blended.
Reduce heat very low.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture starts to bubble at edges.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemonade.
Cover and chill until firm (overnight).
Blend remainder of sugar and berries.
Garnish custard with berries.

title: divine raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in boiling pineapple juice and water. Pour over marshmallows and cream cheese.
Beat with mixer.
Whip the cream; add sugar and vanilla.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Fold in crushed pineapple and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Allow to set. Dissolve raspberry gelatin in two cups boiling water.
Add berries; cool.
Spoon over first layer.
Refrigerate and let set. Serves 10 to 12.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple, pudding mix, and oranges together; fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Chill.

title: fudge
directions: Combine in saucepan; bring to full boil.
Boil for 2 to 3 minutes for icing, 3 to 4 minutes for candy.
Beat until thick. Pour into buttered dish.

title: hamburger bake
directions: Crumble hamburger in large casserole dish.
Combine soups with wire whisk and pour over meat.
You do not have to stir, but I usually do to break my meat up in smaller pieces.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over noodles.

title: sweet spiced nuts
directions: In a bowl, combine nuts and egg white.
In a large bowl, combine sugar and spices.
Toss nuts in the sugar mixture; spread out on a baking sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes, shaking 3 or 4 times.
Cool nuts and store in airtight container.

title: mushroom melody
directions: In large skillet at a medium heat, simmer oil, chopped mushrooms, garlic, parsley, lemon pepper, salt, basil and butter. Stir until mushrooms are golden and tender.
Add wine and shortly after sprinkle flour.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat for five minutes.
Add a splash of wine.
Serve over linguini cooked according to package.
This is also delicious over tender veal.

title: never fail punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 6 cups boiling water.
Mix lemonade according to directions on can.
(Might be better to reduce water by 1/2 cup for each can lemonade.)
Add to Jell-O and stir thoroughly.
Pour over the ice in punch bowl.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Freeze ice in molds ahead of time, any shape molds you desire for the occasion.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt shortening in a saucepan.
Add onion and beef; brown slightly.
Add seasonings, tomato soup and kidney beans.
Cook slowly for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with crisp crackers and relishes.

title: peppermint fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and butter in a heavy saucepan. Bring to boil (rolling boil), stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat or until 234° on candy thermometer.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Cook onions, squash and cloves in broth until soft. Pour mixture into blender or food processor. Add curry and cream. Blend 2 to 3 minutes. Serve sprinkled with parsley. May be prepared early in day and reheated. Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken sour cream enchiladas
directions: In a large saucepan, mix the 2 different kinds of soup, green chilies, chicken and sour cream together.
It will be thick, so you will need to add a little of the broth from the chicken to make it the right consistency, not runny, but not like paste, but in between.

title: buckeyes
directions: Heat in double boiler; dip balls and set on wax paper. Refrigerate.

title: swedish nut cake (pineapple)
directions: Mix together the above ingredients in the order listed.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except the eggs.
Place on a nest of lettuce.
Chill before serving.
Garnish with wedges of hard-boiled eggs.

title: ice box pickles
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well, then add the sugar and vinegar.
Let set for 1 hour put in jars or plastic containers and refrigerate.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add soup, cheese, shrimp and mushrooms.
Mix and heat in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Save some of grated cheese, sprinkle on top the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread half of mixture in baking dish, layer sliced cheese on top of corn mixture. Repeat layers.

title: apple ring cucumber pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in a crock and add pickling lime and enough water to cover cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and soak 2 hours in clear cold ice water.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, red food coloring and enough water (in pan) to cover cucumbers.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Drain.

title: buttermilk crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, margarine and cream of tartar together like pie crumbs, keeping 1/2 cup for topping.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 2 pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, depending on depth of pans.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream
together butter and sugar; add eggs and molasses and beat
well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternately with milk. Drop
from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: braciola
directions: Mince
garlic
and parsley together; add to this grated cheese,
salt
and	pepper	to
taste.
On each slice of steak spread mixture.
Add strips of meat fat if desired.
Roll each slice
and	secure	with
toothpicks.
Brown
in
pan.
Add to tomato
sauce and let simmer until sauce is done.
When tomato sauce
is
not being used, add chopped onion and white wine to Braciola; simmer until tender.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Saute onion
(in
bacon fat, if desired).
Combine all ingredients.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in upper part of double boiler. Add salt and nuts and drop from tip of a tsp. onto waxed paper. Set aside to harden.

title: meringue pie
directions: Beat the egg whites stiff and add the sugar, vanilla and almond extracts, baking powder and chopped nuts. Fold in the crushed Ritz crackers. Bake in a well-greased 9-inch pie pan for 30 minutes at 300°. Top with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: mushroom scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender and drain.
Put in a greased baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup, cheese, pimento, salt and milk together. Pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Melt butter in sauce pan.
Cool.
Then beat eggs well.
Add sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Add flour, coconut and milk, stirring until mixed well.
Pour into two 9 inch pie plates. Crust forms during baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: heritage hill's pink lemonade
directions: Cut lemons; discard seeds.
In a large bowl, press with a wooden meat tenderizer or mallet.
Add sugar, water and mashed maraschino cherries.
Add ice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: brown velvet molasses cookies
directions: Place 1 tablespoon soda in milk and 1 in molasses.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add molasses and milk. Mix alternately with flour, about 6 cups.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour and roll out.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes. Frost with powdered sugar and add orange flavoring.

title: garlic roasted potatoes(serves 6)
directions: Preheat oven to hot 450°.
Melt butter and cook garlic for 2 minutes.
Toss potatoes with garlic butter, salt, pepper and onions.
Pour onto heavy cookie sheets, leaving room around each piece, to allow heat to cook evenly.
Roast, turning after 15 minutes, until all sides are crisp and golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: beef roast in mushroom sauce
directions: Combine in medium bowl with wire whisk the soups and soup mix. On a large sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil, pour 1/2 of the soup mixture; place meat on top.
Spread the meat with remaining soup mixture.
Wrap the meat tightly.
Bake the roast at 350° for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Remove the gravy to a saucepan; add 2 tablespoons sour cream, if desired, and serve over sliced meat.

title: mary's trifle
directions: Layer sliced angel food cake and thawed frozen strawberries. Repeat layer.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream. Add mashed potatoes gradually. Put in casserole and add butter on top. Refrigerate. Heat in 350° oven for about 1 hour when needed.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, Worcestershire sauce, egg and pepper.
In baking dish, shape meat into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Cook sausage and drain well.
Cool completely.
Mix cheese, biscuit mix and water.
Add sausage and mix with fork until blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Puffs can be made ahead and frozen after baking.
Reheat in 375° oven.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased pie dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Makes 2 small or 1 large pie.

title: carol's poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook
chicken and remove from bones.
Place in a casserole dish.
Mix
in
sour
cream
and
cream of chicken soup. Crush Ritz crackers and moisten with the butter.
Place on top of chicken and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of margarine on bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt; pour over margarine. Spread peach mixture on top of batter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for two hours.
Serve with corn chips.

title: 5 minute fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit juices, then add 1 cup of the juice with the pudding.
Then add lemon juice.
Fold into fruit.

title: golden squash bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine eggs, cottage cheese, flour and bouillon. Add squash; mix well. Turn into greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish. Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: crepe batter
directions: Combine and mix the eggs and salt with mixer or wire whip until smooth. Gradually add flour alternately with milk. Beat until smooth. Add the butter. Brush oil very lightly on skillet every 4th crepe. Use 1-ounce ladle. Turn to smooth over very thin; brown, turn and brown.

title: icing in the cake
directions: Add all ingredients except the icing. When mixed well, stir in the icing. Put in Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli macaroni
directions: *Mixture of 1/2 teaspoon each:
dried parsley, basil and garlic powder.

title: rhubarb pudding cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to instructions on the box.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into large cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: polish chicken with sour cream dill gravy
directions: Heat butter; saute onions or shallots for 4 minutes.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Remove onions and saute chicken until lightly browned and cooked through.
Remove coated chicken. Return onions to pan.
Stir in sour cream and dill until hot. Arrange chicken on platter.
Pour cream mix over.
Garnish with fresh dill.

title: herb-cooked halibut
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Have a baking sheet ready.
In a small bowl, mix bread crumbs, cheese, onion, parsley, basil and cloves. Stir in butter with a fork until mixture is evenly moistened.
Tear off four 12-inch squares of foil.
Lightly coat 1 side with vegetable spray or oil.
Place a fish steak on each.
Drizzle with oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with prepared crumb mixture.
Spoon wine around each fish steak.
Fold foil and seal edges securely.
Arrange packets on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 minutes or until done.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Serve with parslied noodles sprinkled with grated lemon peel, sliced tomatoes and red onions and mixed fruit compote.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together soups and rice and put in baking dish.
Save 2 or 3 spoonfuls to spread over top of chicken.
Push chicken down in mixture and spoon remaining rice mixture over top.
Some water may need to be added to soup mixture to keep from getting dry.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Soften ice cream. When this is done, spread in crust.
Freeze until firm.
Spread caramel over top. Next put nuts on top. Cover with Cool Whip. Freeze for 4 hours. Very good and easy.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Drain all canned items.
Mix all vegetables together gently. Mix the vinegar and sugar; pour over vegetables.
Chill.
Best prepared 24 hours in advance.

title: turner's clam chowder
directions: Wash clams thoroughly.
Place quahogs in pot with 1/2 cup water.
Cover tightly and steam until clams open.
Repeat process with cherrystones.
Remove clams from shells and chop coarsely. Reserve broth in separate container.
In the same pot, add clarified butter and garlic.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add onion, celery and spices.
Saute until onion is translucent.
Add flour to make roux, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes (don't brown).
Slowly add clam juice (fresh and bottled), stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Simmer for 10 minutes (the soup will be very thick, so be careful not to burn).
Add potatoes and cook until tender.
Add cream and clams; bring back to a boil.
Season to taste.
Serves 10.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add milk and dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Mix in vanilla.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Brown meat; add onions, celery and green pepper.
Cook noodles until almost done; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
When done, add parsley on top.
Serves 6.

title: frosting
directions: Bring milk to a boil in saucepan and set aside to cool (but not cold).
While milk is cooling, cream together in bowl, margarine, Crisco shortening, granulated sugar and vanilla.
Add milk to this and beat and beat and beat and beat.
It may look like it won't work, but it will come together.
Beat until you get the thickness of a creamy frosting.

title: apple-peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine chocolate, Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla; set aside.
Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan. Combine sugar and apple juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook until soft-ball stage (240° on candy thermometer), stirring often.
Remove from heat; quickly add the chocolate mixture.
Stir just until blended. Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with chopped peanuts, if desired.
Cut when firm.
Makes about 40 pieces.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cut chicken up in small pieces.
Mix chicken broth, soup, onion and stuffing together.
Save croutons.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the croutons on top.
Then put 1/2 cup chicken broth on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Put spaghetti in the bottom of a large pan.
Mix all the other ingredients (except the black olives) together and pour over spaghetti.
Top with black olives.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 10 to 12.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add eggs and blend well.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat into mixture.
Roll 1/4 inch thick and cut out.
(These do better if dough is chilled for a short time.)
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and decorate as desired.

title: giardiniera
directions: Combine cauliflower, carrots, pepper rings, and bell pepper in a bowl.
In a small saucepan, add sugar, vinegar, mustard seeds, peppercorns and heat over a low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour marinade over vegetables and refrigerate, stirring occasionally for at least 24 hours.
Drain and serve. Makes 1 quart.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Makes two pies.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In medium bowl, stir strawberries, eggs and oil.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add berry mixture to dry ingredients and mix just until blended.
Pour into pans. Bake 1 hour or until tests done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: microwave reuben meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together, using only 1/4 cup tomato soup. Place in glass baking dish with glass in center. Mix sauerkraut and 1/2 cup shredded swiss cheese. Press into meat center about 1 inch. Cover with wax paper. Microwave on medium-high 18 minutes. Let stand for 5-6 minutes. Combine leftover tomato soup and horseradish. Mix well. Spread over Reuben loaf and cook on medium-high for 6-8 minutes. Place cheese triangles on top. Heat for 2-3 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: ham and zucchini frittata
directions: In a 10-inch covered skillet, saute zucchini and onions in hot oil until lightly browned.
Remove from pan.
Beat together eggs, milk, Italian seasoning and salt.
Pour into pan.
Arrange zucchini and ham over egg mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes or until eggs are partially set.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30
minutes
in
a
1/2 x 15 1/2-inch cookie sheet.

title: susan strachan's champion chocolate chip cookies
directions: After measuring, put 1/2 cup oatmeal in a blender until it turns to powder.
Set oatmeal aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to butter mixture.
Then add grated chocolate bar and chips.
Make golf ball sized cookies, placing 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except lettuce and mayonnaise.
Chill. Mix in lettuce and mayonnaise just before serving.

title: lazy gal apple pie
directions: Melt margarine in boiler.
Add applesauce, sugar and flavoring.
Mix well while it heats.
Add bread crumbs; mix well and pour into pie pan or casserole dish and brown in a 400° oven.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. In medium sized mixing bowl beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill several hours.
Top with cherry pie filling and Cool Whip before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until done or set.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown meat until tender; add onions and celery and saute for a few minutes longer.
Add rest of ingredients.
Turn into casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with a tossed salad and French bread.

title: vegetarian roll-ups
directions: Lay out 2 tortilla shells, overlapping all but 2 inches.
Have the top shell close to you.
Spread 1/4 to 3/8 inch slaw over tortilla shell, leaving 1 inch bare on sides.
Sprinkle each vegetable and cheese over cole slaw.
Wrap very tightly, compressing edges well as you roll up.

title: ham and rice
directions: Saute onions, celery, and margarine.
Add soup, wine, mustard, pimentos and seasonings.
Heat, add ham.
Just before serving, add sour cream and pineapple.
Serve over rice.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Together cream margarine, sugar and molasses.
Add vanilla, egg, flour and baking soda.
Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick spiced peaches
directions: Cook all ingredients (except peaches) for 5 minutes.
Add peaches and cook 5 minutes more.
Cool.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: noodles
directions: Mix well and roll out on a floured board, cut in thin strips or roll up and slice very thin, let dry.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes in broth.

title: amy's dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Great with any vegetable.

title: scotchies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and blend.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and stir lightly. Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Measure all ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth. Use as any sweetened condensed milk.
Makes equivalent of 1 can. Economical and convenient.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower and broccoli into flowerettes. Add remaining vegetables. Toss with Italian salad dressing.
Add herbs, such as parsley and mint, if desired.
Chill several hours or overnight.
This keeps well for 5 days.
(To make a luncheon main course, add tuna or cooked chicken or turkey to the salad.) Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken
directions: Cook for 50 minutes in the oven.

title: eggnog(civil war times,  december 24, 1864)
directions: Beat the egg yolks until light, then slowly beat in the sugar, cream, brandy and wine.
Whip the whites separately, then fold into other ingredients.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and serve.

title: almond squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add yolk.
Continue to cream; add flour and almond extract.
Spread batter into 10 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
In small bowl, beat egg white with a fork until foamy.
Brush over top of batter and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chili mix on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Garnish with sliced jalapeno peppers.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with tortilla dipping chips.
A favorite for any party!

title: lemon-mustard sauce
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Serve on prime rib or fish.

title: fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 325° (slow moderate). Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Combine date filling from bar mix package with hot water in large bowl. Add crumbly mix, eggs, flour, baking powder, molasses and spices; blend well. Fold in nuts and fruit thoroughly. Pour into prepared pan. Bake about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean. Cool. Wrap well in aluminum foil. Store in cool place 2 or 3 days before slicing. Glaze after storing. Bring 1/4 cup light corn syrup and 2 tablespoons water to rolling boil. Cool; pour over fruit cake. Decorate top of cake with bits of candied fruit dipping in corn syrup.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Mix peas (juice and all), well drained tuna, Miracle Whip and spices.
Add to drained, cooled macaroni.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: buffalo-style chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off chicken wings.
In a food processor or blender, process soup mix, butter, vinegar, water, garlic, pepper and cumin; set aside.
Broil chicken for 12 minutes or until brown, turning every 6 minutes.
Brush with 1/2 of the soup mixture, then broil 2 minutes, or until crisp.
Turn, then brush with remaining soup mixture; broil an additional minute.
Serve with Blue cheese dressing and celery sticks, if desired.

title: sweet salad dressing
directions: Use equal parts of mayonnaise, milk and sharp cheese.
Heat and keep in double boiler.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions thin, then chop.
Mix onion, water, salt, sugar, paprika and oleo.
Cook until onions are well done.
Add milk but do not boil.
Heat to near simmering stage.
Stir in cheese until cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Fold in saltines (crumbled), vanilla and pecans.
Pour into lightly buttered pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
When cool, cover with whipping cream.
Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.
Chill.

title: tomato and green bean casserole *
directions: Drain tomatoes.
Mix bread with melted butter and set 1/3 cup aside for topping.
Combine crumbs, drained tomatoes, beans, sugar and seasonings.
Bake in shallow dish at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: eggplant caponata
directions: Cube the eggplant into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Fry lightly until brown in 1/2 cup oil.
Place all ingredients together in large spaghetti pot; cook for 1/2 hour, covered, until thick.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove skin and bone from salmon
and
mash
fine.
Mix salmon, salt, pepper, lemon juice,	beaten	egg
yolk, cracker crumbs and hot milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle paprika over
top	and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add 1 cup ice, crushed.
Cool until jelled.
Add sugar, vinegar and pineapple.
Stir and add remaining ingredients.
Pour in pan 12 x 13-inch.
Chill until firm.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, let chill, then roll out.
Cut and bake at 400°.

title: garlic parmesan rolls
directions: Cut dough into 16 pieces; shape into balls.
Place on a floured surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 10 minutes. In a bowl, stir Parmesan cheese and garlic powder in butter. Roll bread ball in butter mixture.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 16 rolls.

title: lemon cooler
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch glass dish with margarine.
Combine margarine and flour.
Press on bottom of pan.
Press nuts on top. Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes.

title: rice pilafhouston, texas
directions: Blend all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Make as many multiplications as you like.
With this mix, you can whip up the following yummy recipe in a matter of minutes.
It tastes great with chicken or grilled vegetables.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: punch for 35
directions: Boil water and sugar 3 minutes.
Float cherries and mint leaves on top for garnish.

title: layered strawberry dessert salad
directions: Beat the cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Gradually add milk and vanilla. Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat to dissolve. Blend into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Chill until firm, about 1/2 hour. Dissolve strawberry and raspberry gelatin in boiling water. Cool.
Mash bananas well. Blend into gelatin. Stir in pineapple and strawberries.
Spoon and spread over cream mixture.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Put half of mixture in 8 x 12-inch dish.
In separate bowl, mix next 6 ingredients.
Spread over bread mixture in casserole dish and top with remaining bread mixture.
Beat eggs slightly and add milk.
Pour over bread mixture; cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Spread soup over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Can sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over top and return to oven for 10 minutes.)

title: lemon-coconut bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour and confectioners sugar, cut in butter until crumbly.
Press into bottom of lightly buttered 9 x 13 inch baking pan; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, granulated sugar, baking powder and lemon juice.
Pour over crust, top with coconut.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool, cut into bars and store in refrigerator.

title: singapore green rice(chinese)
directions: Take cup of raw rice and cook it. Add eggs, milk, salad oil, Tabasco sauce, salt and Cheddar cheese to rice, mixing well. Add rice mixture to green vegetables; mix well. Pour into a large buttered casserole. Top with bread crumbs, grated Parmesan cheese (if desired) and paprika. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. May be prepared a day in advance and cooked before needed.

title: western barbecue sauce
directions: Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes the grated onion and garlic.
Mix chopped raw beef.
Add ketchup, vinegar, salt, paprika, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer gently and stir constantly for 10 minutes.
Serve hot with steak and hamburgers.

title: bunuelos
directions: Blend as a pie pastry; roll small balls into thin circles. Deep-fry in hot oil; sprinkle with extra cinnamon and sugar.
Makes approximately 42 Bunuelos.

title: ribs and kraut
directions: Place kraut in large, flat baking pan and sprinkle generously with brown sugar.
Dab some water over top and lay on the ribs. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for about 4 hours.
Check now and then as you may have to add some water.

title: sausage bread
directions: *Thaw bread; let rise 2 times.
Flatten out like pizza crust. Put on greased cookie sheets until ready for remaining ingredients.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Combine with Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple.
Now combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix together bananas and milk in a low bowl, mashing bananas.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° in 2 greased loaf pans for 45 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp-feta-pasta salad
directions: Mix shrimp, Feta cheese, tomatoes, cucumber, dressing, lemon juice and seasonings.
Toss with prepared pasta.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potato chip cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Grease sheet.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: apple dip
directions: Soften cheese and mix with rest of ingredients.
Let sit for one hour.
Serve with apple slices.

title: angel salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and reserve juice.
In a double boiler combine sugar, egg, juice, vinegar and salt.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and let stand 1 hour.
Add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix with first ingredients, beat well and add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until done in oblong pan.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, oats, corn syrup, butter and coconut.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: spaghetti
directions: Boil the spaghetti.
Put margarine, when the spaghetti is almost done.
Put the cooked spaghetti in a strainer.
Put oil in frying pan.
Saute the garlic and onion; put in the ground beef. When ground beef is done, add the following ingredients; pepper, salt, tomato sauce and ketchup.
Add chicken broth, green pepper, sausage or hot dog and sugar.
Simmer 15 minutes (low fire).

title: breakfast bake
directions: You can make this very low-fat and low-calorie by using fat-free bread, 8 egg whites, 4 egg yolks, skim milk and low-fat cheese.

title: bacon crackers
directions: Cut bacon strips in half.
Wrap 1/2 strip around cracker lengthwise.
Place on baking pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.

title: poached orange roughy
directions: In skillet, heat lemon juice.
Add the orange roughy.
Cover and poach 3 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.
Serve with fresh lemon and black pepper.

title: double fudge brownies
directions: In a saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water until it begins to boil.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat.
Combine all dry ingredients slowly into the saucepan.
Add vanilla, morsels and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix together cream cheese, melted oleo and powdered sugar.
Spread over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
After cake cools 10 minutes, turn out on pan or board.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt.
Beat egg in measuring cup and add ice water to equal 1/2 cup.
Pour in vinegar; mix well.
Add to flour mixture and mix until flour is moist.
Chill.
Divide dough into 3 balls (makes 3 crusts).
Roll to desired size of pan. Unused portion may be frozen.
Frozen dough will roll and handle better than when first mixed.

title: sweet and sour tofu
directions: Drain tofu and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Combine flour, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Dip each tofu cube in batter.
Deep fat fry in oil until golden brown.
Drain and keep warm in oven.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: Brown beef with garlic. Saute carrots, onions, celery, basil and parsley with 2 teaspoons margarine until vegetables are tender. Add potatoes, broth and beef. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes. In skillet, melt 2 teaspoons margarine. Add flour. Cook and whisk for 3 to 5 minutes or until bubbly. Add to soup; bring to boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Reduce to low; add cheese, milk, salt and pepper. Stir and cook until cheese melts. Blend in sour cream. Sprinkle a little cheese on top in individual bowls for color. Enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients.
Combine the egg, melted butter, hot water, orange juice and orange rind.
Add to dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Add the whole cranberries and chopped walnuts.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325° in 2 well-greased 1-pound loaf pans or one 2-pound loaf pan.
Chill, wrap and refrigerate or freeze.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine 2 tablespoons Crisco oil and 3/4 cup warm milk.
Add milk mixture, along with the yeast to dry ingredients.
Mix well; knead 5 to 7 minutes.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise 1 hour and bake at 425° until brown.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, oil and buttermilk in large bowl and mix well.
Add sweet potatoes (which have been sweetened with sugar and melted butter).
Beat until fluffy.
Knead on floured paper.
Pat out and cut.
Place in buttered pans.
Grease tops with melted butter.
Bake in hot oven (450° to 500°) until done.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add oil, bananas, etc.
Mix all with a spoon.
Bake in a 9 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a salad bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sally lunn
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add milk to beaten egg yolks and add to dry ingredients, stirring until mixed.
Stir in butter, then fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in well greased 9-inch square pan.

title: grandma spinks' breakfast pudding
directions: Place bread cubes in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Melt cheese, butter and margarine.
Pour over bread.
Beat eggs well; add milk and pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes to one hour until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda. Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes. Cookies will be puffy, but collapse while cooling. Transfer to waxed paper and sprinkle with powdered sugar when completely cooled.
Store in airtight container with slice of bread so cookies remain chewy.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Place crescent roll dough on a cookie sheet, pinching seams together.
Bake according to package directions.
Cream together cream cheese, Hellmann's mayonnaise, onion and dill weed.
Spread over the crust when it has cooled.
Top with veggies.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter.
Steam broccoli until partially cooked, 3 minutes.
Cool and press dry.
Beat eggs and milk until frothy.
Thoroughly mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture, mixing well.
Fold in broccoli, cheese and onion.
Spoon into baking dish.
Spread even.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 35 minutes or until set and lightly brown.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Makes 4 dozen 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper.
In greased (with butter) 2-quart casserole, arrange layers of potatoes, ham, onion and soup.
Be sure ham is covered to prevent drying.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
You can substitute 1 cup diced chicken for ham.
Makes 6 servings.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except the sugar and eggs. Cook over boiling water for 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and stir in 2 slightly beaten egg yolks. Return to heat and cook 2 minutes more, stirring constantly. Cook and pour into a 9-inch baked pastry shell.	Make meringue of 2 egg whites, folding in 1/4 cup sugar.
Brown meringue.	Cool slightly to serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in small cubes.
Cook with onion for 5 minutes. Drain.

title: white cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk together and cook for 3 minutes. Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add graham cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Fry bacon.
When almost done, drain off grease and add butter, melted.
Saute onions with bacon and set aside.
Cook lasagne noodles and drain.
Cook potatoes; drain.
Then mash smooth.
Add cream cheese and Cheddar cheese to mashed potatoes, mixing well. Add half of bacon, onion and butter mixture to mashed potatoes, mixing well.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer noodles, then potato mixture.
Repeat, ending with lasagne noodles.
Pour remaining butter and onion mixture over all.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: chicken in foil(4 servings)
directions: Place 3 tablespoons of rice in center of 4 (12-inch) squares of heavy-duty aluminum wrap.
Sprinkle chicken on both sides with salt; place on rice.
Drain mushrooms and reserve 1/4 cup liquid. Divide mushrooms, zucchini, green pepper and onion into 4 equal portions; place each portion over each chicken quarter.
Mix together the tomato sauce, reserved mushroom liquid, hot pepper sauce, oregano and basil; spoon over vegetables and chicken.
Fold over food; seal tightly.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Dice cheese and set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine Worcestershire sauce, mustard, cayenne, paprika and beer.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill thoroughly.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Steam broccoli and cut in small pieces.
Saute onions in butter.
Combine all ingredients and pour in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: oriental sweet and sour balls
directions: Mix and shape in 1-inch balls.
Brown slowly; pour off fat. May be frozen for advanced preparation.

title: easy pecan bars
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside 1 cup of the cake mix for the filling.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat sugar and margarine until creamy.
Beat in egg until light and fluffy. Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chopped Butterfinger chips
Drop dough by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand on cookie sheet for 2 minutes.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: mardi gras punch
directions: Do not dilute juices.
Mix all together.
When ready to serve, put sherbet balls on top of juices.
Add ginger ale and mix.
Serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine the sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart shallow casserole pan.
Combine the brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup of butter and pecans.
Sprinkle over the casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (325° if you use a glass dish).

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend together butter, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over top of dough.
Place in oven at 375° for 1 minute.
Remove from oven; run knife through dough to marbleize.
Return to oven and bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix melted margarine with pretzels and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° and cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together and put on top of pretzel crust.
Dissolve 2 packages of Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup of pineapple juice.
Let stand until it starts to gel (put in freezer).
Mix with large can of crushed pineapple, drained.
Add strawberries cut up.
Spread on top of cream cheese.
Layers:
Bottom pretzels, then cream cheese, strawberries and Jell-O.)

title: spicy spinach potatoes
directions: Fry bacon; drain and set aside.
Cook spinach; drain and set aside.
Boil potatoes; drain and mash.
Then add spinach to potatoes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes; set aside.
In large saucepan combine water, beef and chicken broth, undrained tomatoes, onion and green pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken, reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add corn, cumin, chili powder and pepper.
Simmer covered for 10 minutes more.
To serve, place crushed tortilla chips into each bowl.
Ladle soup over chips. Sprinkle with cheese.
Add sliced avocado if desired.

title: graham cracker cupcakes
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and egg yolks together.
Add milk, walnuts or pecans, vanilla and crackers.
Beat egg whites until fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Fold into batter with spoon.
Bake in lined muffin tin for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: popeye biscuits
directions: Mix sour cream and sprite and mix into bisquick. Roll out dough and cut into biscuits. Melt 1 stick of butter in pan. Dip biscuit in butter and bake in oven.

title: meatball meal for one
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add meat; mix well.
Shape into 4 meatballs; set aside.
Combine potato and carrot in a 2 1/2-cup casserole; sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, drain and mash them.
Mix in sour cream and cream cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 12 x 8-inch dish at 325° for 35 minutes.
Add paprika and cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: jane's extra easy strawberry pie
directions: Cook and cool pie shell.
Beat cream cheese, vanilla and Marshmallow Creme until creamy.
Place in pie shell and cover with fresh sliced strawberries.
(Do not sugar strawberries unless serving immediately as strawberries will weep).
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
This filling is good for any fruit (i.e. blueberries or peaches).

title: wassail (hot christmas punch)
directions: Tie in cheesecloth bag the 16 cloves, whole allspice and cinnamon stick, broken into pieces.
Stud 3 oranges with box of cloves; cover well.
In saucepan, combine apple juice or cider, cranberry juice, sugar and bitters.
Add bag of spices and oranges; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add rum just before serving.
Garnish with slice of orange for each cup.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: la porte hot chicken salad
directions: Mix salad dressing and lemon juice.
Add all the ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole; top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: corn beef cheese roll
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Make into ball or long roll.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill until time to serve.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni; set aside.
Melt butter in a 2-quart glass casserole in microwave (about 1 minute on High).
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly. Cook, uncovered, for 6 minutes at High; stir every 2 minutes.
Add cheese to sauce; stir.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave 1 minute at High.
Add cooked macaroni to cheese sauce; mix.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave 8 minutes at Medium-high.
Stir halfway through cooking period.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Mix until smooth.
Bake in waffle iron according to manufacturers directions.
Makes 10 to 12 waffles.

title: impossible pie
directions: Grease a pie pan with margarine; set aside.
Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat for 2 to 3 minutes and pour into pie pan.
Wait 2 minutes and sprinkle coconut all over top.
Bake in the oven at 400° for about 30 minutes.
Pie will rise up and split on top.
The top will be very brown.

title: company cheese cake
directions: To make crust, mix together graham cracker crumbs, walnuts, cinnamon and butter.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of this mixture for top.
Press remainder on bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
To make filling, combine eggs, cheese, sugar, salt and flavorings; beat until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and pour into crust.
Trim with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Cool and chill for 4 to 5 hours.

title: diabetic sugarless cake
directions: Combine raisins in water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Add beaten egg. Add soft shortening, rolled oats, sweetener and vanilla. Sift the flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix all together well.
Pour into greased layer cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked gourmet chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, combine chicken, celery and French dressing. Marinate for 1 hour.
To chicken mixture, add 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese, grapes and almonds.
Blend together sour cream, mustard and salt; pour over chicken mixture and toss lightly to blend. Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Combine cracker crumbs and 1 cup cheese.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: tuna spinach braid
directions: Combine spinach, tuna, cottage cheese and garlic; set aside. Unroll crescent rolls onto floured board; do not separate.
Press to seal seams (perforations).
Lightly flour top and roll to form 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Transfer to 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Spread filling down center of dough lengthwise in 3 1/2-inch strip. Top with cheese.
Make cuts in dough at 1-inch intervals on both sides of rectangle almost to edge of filling.
Fold dough strips diagonally over filling, overlapping strips and alternating from side to side.
Top will look braided.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs with molasses and sugar, add dry ingredients. Stir in
buttermilk.
Bake
at
for 45 to 50 minutes or until middle is set.
This makes 4 (8-inch) pies.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in large mixing bowl. Mix all well and pour into loaf tin that has been greased, 5 x 9-inch. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan for 15 minutes. Remove to cool.

title: golden delight pancakes
directions: Beat eggs slightly; sift dry ingredients.
Add butter or oleo and milk to eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat only until all flour is mixed.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: jalapeno chicken enchiladas
directions: In each of two greased 13 x 9 baking dishes, spread 1/2 cup of tomato sauce; set aside. In a large bowl, combine the soup, sour cream, jalapenos, onion salt and pepper. Stir in chicken and 2 cups of cheese. Spread about 1/2 cup chicken mixture down the center of each tortilla. Roll up and place seam side down in prepared dishes. Top with remaining tomato sauce; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and bake one casserole at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cover and freeze remaining casserole for up to 1 month.

title: french country chicken
directions: Thaw and drain frozen vegetables.
Combine all vegetables and add 1/2 can French fried onions.
Skin chicken breasts.
Place vegetables in the bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken breasts.
In a small bowl combine wine, bouillon, garlic salt and pepper; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes or until chicken is done.
Baste chicken with wine sauce and top with remaining onions.
Bake an additional 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water, then add cold water. Let thicken; fold in pineapple, bananas and marshmallows. Refrigerate. Mix together beaten egg, sugar, flour and pineapple juice. Cook until thick. Add cream cheese and stir until smooth. Let cool, then fold cream cheese mixture into whipped topping. Spread over Jell-O. Top with coconut. Do not cover.

title: cold nacho dip
directions: Blend together the sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread bean dip on plate.
Next spread avocado mixture on, then sour cream mixture.
Top with other items to your taste.

title: better than ever banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Slice 2 bananas and dip in lemon juice; drain.
Arrange on bottom of prepared crust.
Pour filling over bananas.
Cover and chill 4 hours or until set.
Spread top with whipped cream or Cool Whip, if desired, but is very good without topping.
If whipped cream is used, garnish top with more banana slices.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: In heavy skillet, brown chops in small amount hot shortening. Pour off fat.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: crock-pot chicken breasts
directions: Wrap piece of bacon around chicken breast and lay it on a piece of dried beef in your crock-pot.
Do the same for each breast.
You can put as many as you need in your crock-pot.
Cover with 1 can cream of mushroom soup, mixed with 1/3 cup sour cream. Put on low for 8 hours.
