Very good and very moist.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots about 5 minutes in salted water; drain and rinse to cool.
In a saucepan, mix soup and remaining ingredients.
Heat over medium heat for 15 minutes, until thick.
Put carrots in bowl.
Pour soup mixture over carrots and refrigerate overnight.

title: crowd pleaser
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Drain.
Add green chilies, beans, chicken soup and water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Layer the corn tortillas or Fritos on bottom, then beef mixture, alternating until all are gone.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Freeze or bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: georgia peach cobbler(serves 8)
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, flour and nutmeg in a Dutch oven; set aside to allow syrup to form for approximately 15 minutes.
Bring peaches to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes, or until peaches are tender.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and margarine.
Roll 1/2 of pastry to 1/8-inch thickness; cut into circle to fit 2-quart baking dish.
Spoon 1/2 of peach mixture into lightly buttered dish.
Top with pastry.
Bake at 475° for 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Spoon remaining peach mixture over baked pastry.
Roll remaining pastry to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into 1-inch strips.
Arrange in lattice design over peaches. Bake additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Allow to cool slightly.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: energy bars
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together. Cream together sugar and shortening. Add molasses and egg; mix well. Sift flour and spices together. Add fruit mixture and mix well. Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325°. Bake for 35 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Sift soda with 1/2 of flour and blend in.
Add all spices.
Add remaining flour to fruit and nuts and blend in.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 14 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: dingbats
directions: Melt margarine, dates and sugar for 8 minutes in a saucepan. Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Roll mixture into balls and dip in powdered sugar.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients, mashing dates continuously. Cook for only 6 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add 2 3/4 cups Rice Krispies, 1 cup chopped pecans and 1 tsp. vanilla. Form in small balls and roll in coconut.

title: festive fruit compote
directions: Drain pears, reserving 1/2 c. syrup.
Drain apricot syrup into large sauce pan; add pear syrup.
Stir in sugar, lemon peel, juice and cinnamon stick.
Bring to a boil; simmer gently for 5 mintues. Add pears, apricots and plums; heat throughly.
Serve compote warm or chilled.
Serves 8.

title: marinated broccoli slaw
directions: Can also use 5 cups green cabbage, chopped.

title: broiled pork chops
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first 9 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Set aside half of the sauce.
Place the pork chops on broiling pan rack.
Broil about 4 in. from the heat for 4 minutes on each side. Brush with remaining sauce.
Continue broiling, turning, and basting occasionally, for 3-4 minutes or until juices run clear. Serve with reserved sauce.

title: claremont casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
Saute onion and green pepper in shortening.
Add meat and stir.
Blend mushroom soup and milk together; combine all ingredients together.
Bake in a casserole for 1 hour in a 360° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook beef.
Add onions, garlic powder, tomato sauce and olives.
Combine sour cream, cottage cheese and chilies.
Crush tortilla chips.
Place a third of the chips in bottom of 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Layer in order with half the meat mixture, half the sour cream mixture and half the grated cheese; repeat layers, ending with final third of crushed tortilla chips.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hershey marble cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
*Grate chocolate bar.
Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream and oil for 4 minutes.
Pour syrup into separate bowl and stir in 2 tablespoons batter.
In greased Bundt pan, layer with 1/3 batter, 1/2 of chocolate batter, 1/2 of grated chocolate two times, then top with remaining batter.
Bake approximately 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove carefully.
When cold, sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables and add liquid.
Then add Italian dressing and set overnight.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and roll in balls.
Roll in sugar and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut up artichokes into a bowl.
Add mayo and Parmesan cheese. Crush and dice garlic; then add.
Put ingredients into a pie pan and bake at 350° until top is golden brown.
Use with white tortilla chips or Fritos as a dip.

title: spinach salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine spinach, sprouts and water chestnuts. Add bacon, cover and refrigerate.
In a jar, combine oil, sugar, vinegar, catsup, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Shake or stir to blend.
Cover and chill.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; combine with onions, soup and sour cream.
Melt margarine and mix with half of stuffing.
Place on bottom of 9 x 13-inch or 3-quart baking dish.
Add half of the squash mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Add remaining squash and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: orange-carrot cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add carrots, egg and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to carrot mixture.
Mix well.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pack into a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
For a drier loaf, add more bread crumbs.
Serve with tartar sauce and lemon wedges.

title: filled cupcakes
directions: Mix together cake mix according to instructions on box.
Fill cupcake pans halfway.
Combine remaining ingredients together and spoon on top of cupcake dough.
Cover with remaining dough.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream, corn syrup and salt.
Boil to soft ball stage (260°).
Add vanilla.
Do not cool, but beat immediately with electric mixer until creamy and begins to hold its shape (about 10 minutes).
Thoroughly mix in remaining ingredients.
Press into buttered 9 X 13 pan.
Chill until firm enough ro cut.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.
This keeps very well.

title: lo-cal cranberry jewel salad
directions: Place cranberry juice cocktail and orange juice in a nonaluminum saucepan.
Sprinkle gelatin over juice mixture.
Let stand 1 minute.
Add honey.
Cook, over low heat, stirring, until gelatin and honey dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cranberries, celery and mandarin oranges.
Spoon gelatin mixture into a 4-cup mold, coated with cooking spray.
Cover and chill until firm.
Unmold salad onto a lettuce-lined serving platter.

title: mrs. bischoff's chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Carefully put a slit in the side of each breast half with a sharp knife.
Fill with as many slices of Jack cheese as will comfortably fit.
Fasten with toothpicks so the cheese won't melt out while cooking.
Mix together eggs, Parmesan cheese, and parsley.
Roll the chicken in flour, coating heavily, and then dip in the egg mixture.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken bone and grind. Cook beef, pork, and onion in chicken stock and then grind. Add all ingredients. Cook slowly 1 hour and stir often.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add onion; mix well. Then add egg and buttermilk. Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease and fry until they float. Drain on paper towels.

title: easy baked chicken kiev
directions: Place chicken breasts, one at a time, between 2 sheets of wax paper or plastic wrap. With flat side of a mallet, gently pound breasts until each is about 1/4-inch thick.
Set aside.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put everything in a bowl; mix by hand.
Let set in refrigerator, then serve.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: In a large pan, brown beef (drain). Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes, or until the peppers and rice are done.

title: fire and ice pickles
directions: Combine pickles, sugar, hot sauce and pepper flakes in large bowl.
Cover; let stand 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Spoon pickles into jars.
Add a clove of garlic to each jar.
Cover with metal lids and screw on bands.
Refrigerate.
Yields 3 pints.
The longer they sit, the more bite to them.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add pimiento, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and seasonings; mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball; roll in chopped pecans.
For variety, you can roll this cheese ball in finely chopped parsley, dried beef or chopped, toasted almonds.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Prepare chocolate cake batter as directed.
Spoon into 18 greased or paper-lined muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Remove papers, if used.
Spread Cool Whip on bottom and sides of cupcakes.
Press coconut into whipped topping.
Place cupcakes, top sides down, on serving plate. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 18.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix with pimento cheese and dressing.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts. Refrigerate in tight container.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients by hand.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 325° until set, but not brown.
Cool and roll in sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy, then add sugar, oil and vanilla; beat well. Stir in zucchini. Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices. Add flour mixture to zucchini mixture. Fold in nuts. Pour into 2 greased, floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cool before serving. Yields 2 loaves.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Thoroughly clean seeds.
Cover with lightly salted water and soak for 1 to 2 hours.
Pour seeds into strainer, discarding soaking water.
Lay seeds in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°, stirring occasionally, until dry/crisp, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch to prevent burning.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Cream butter with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 2 tablespoons cocoa, 1/2 cup evaporated milk, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 box powdered sugar and beat well after each addition.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
While cake is still warm, spread with following topping.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine together.
Add sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: fettuccine alfredo with variations
directions: These should be added shortly before tossing with noodles (5 to 10 minutes).

title: red caviar cheese ball
directions: Beat the cheeses in small mixer bowl until smooth. Refrigerate, covered, until firm.
Form cheese mixture into ball. Place on serving plate.
Coat cheese ball with sour cream.
Press caviar into surface of ball.
Do not break grain of caviar. Served with sliced rye bread.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain well.
Mash and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ham loaf, pepper, eggs, cracker crumbs and milk.
Mix well.
Form into balls and place in baking pan.
Mix sugar, mustard, vinegar and water.
Pour over balls in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, and 1 hour, uncovered.
Double sauce mixture if you desire more juice.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, brown sugar, egg and 1/3 cup peanut butter. Add baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and rolled oats.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Upon removing from oven, immediately sprinkle with 1 cup chocolate bits.
Let stand 5 minutes to soften.
Spread evenly over crust.
Cool.
Combine powdered sugar, 1/4 cup peanut butter and enough milk to make spreadable.
Drizzle over chocolate.
Cool.
Cut into bars to serve.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Boil kielbasa for 15 to 20 minutes.
While this is cooking, simmer the jelly and pineapple.
Drain kielbasa and rinse with hot water.
Combine with jelly mixture, simmer until thickened.

title: calico meringues
directions: Preheat oven to 250° (120°C).
Grease and flour a large baking sheet.

title: chocolate pecan pralines(from hershey's 1934 chocolate cookbook)
directions: Combine sugars, cream and salt in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to 228° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat and add baking chocolate, broken into small pieces, butter and pecans.
Return to heat, stirring constantly and cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and add vanilla; cool 5 minutes.
Beat 10 to 15 seconds or until slightly thickened.
Quickly drop candy by large spoonfuls onto greased plates or waxed paper.
If mixture becomes too thick to drop, stir in a tablespoonful of hot water.
Yields 18 to 20
medium pralines.

title: crab meat canapes
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix crab meat, mayo and seasoning together.
Toast cuts of bread on 1 side.
Pile crab meat mixture on untoasted side of bread.
Place under broiler until hot and slightly brown.

title: pumpkin ring dessert
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients in order given.
Add water, butter and eggs; mix well.
Add nuts, raisins and pumpkin.
Pour into 2-quart ring mold or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Packs well for shipping.

title: mandel bread
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Makes 5 rolls.
Place rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in diagonal slices. Bake at 400° until lightly browned, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cherries and sliced orange. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with the orange slice and cherry in each serving.
(Of course, you will "fish out" the stick of cinnamon and whole cloves.)

title: corn dip
directions: Mix together and serve with tortilla chips.

title: shirley's banana cake
directions: Batter:
Mix the cake mix, eggs, water, 1/2 container sour cream and 1 1/2 mashed bananas (mashed by using bottom of a small glass).
Use mixer on batter until lumps of cake mix have dissolved.
Pour batter into two 9-inch round pans or 1 large oblong pan.
I use wax paper on round pans.
Bake as box directs.

title: banana pudding
directions: Hand mix pudding and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra; pack in jars.
Put 1 pepper and 1 clove garlic in each jar.
Heat vinegar, water and salt to boiling.
Celery seed or mustard seed may be added for flavor.
Pour liquid over okra; fill and seal.
Don't use for 8 weeks.

title: hobo pack
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make patty of ground beef.
Peel and slice vegetables.
Place on aluminum foil.
Bring corners up and twist to cover.
Place in oven on a baking pan and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Serves 1.

title: party cake
directions: Mix cake; put on cookie sheet pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Mix milk and pudding.
Spread on cool cake.
Spread drained pineapple on pudding.
Mix; spread Cool Whip on top. Cover with coconut and nuts.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Do not pare cucumbers.
Slice thin; place in a large bowl. Add onions and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt; cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours; drain thoroughly.

title: the church ladies punch
directions: Chill tea and Sprite. Put in punch bowl and add lemonade concentrate. Stir to mix. Add garnish and serve.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round layer pans, 8 or 9-inch.
Mix all ingredients on low speed for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Pour batter into pans; bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: low-fat fudge(first place)
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
In a large saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in milk and sugar and bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove pan from heat and stir in chocolate.
Add prunes, Marshmallow Creme, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into pan and chill.
Cut into 48 pieces when firm.

title: ok cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and baking powder together. Beat eggs and shortening together. Add milk. Roll out and cut cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: slumgullion
directions: Brown beef in skillet over moderate heat.
Add onion as meat begins to brown.
Drain
off
fat; add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring to
a boil, reduce heat and cook 1 hour or more. Stir
occasionally.
Mixture
should
be
thick when done. Vegetables should be
tender.
If
you
prefer it to be more like soup, add more water.

title: uncle johnny's popovers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill cupcake tins 3/4 of the way full. Place in cold oven.
Set oven at 450° for 30 minutes. Don't peek.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain and place in greased casserole pan -- (Dish).
Cover meat with undiluted Cream of Chicken soup.
Place layer of Tater Tots over soup and bake at 400 degrees until bubbly.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° in layer cake pans for 45 minutes.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables,
soup,
cup cheese and 1/2 can onion rings.
Put
in quart casserole.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into freezer container. Freeze.
Remove from freezer several hours before serving.

title: margaret's kringla
directions: Mix until smooth.
Take small amount (1/2 cup) and roll with hands into a long strip, curling it into a figure 8. Let them lay on your counter until you get lots made.
Boil a large kettle of water.
Place each Kringla in the boiling water until it floats to the top (like donuts).
Remove them and place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 15 minutes depending on the size you make.
Best fresh with butter!

title: coconut pecan cookies
directions: Combine sugars, butter, oil, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add salt, soda and cream of tartar to flour; add to creamed mixture. Mix the other 4 ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until brown.

title: potato souffle
directions: Peel potatoes, cut into pieces and boil in water until soft (25 to 30 minutes).
Drain potatoes well.
Add onion, milk, butter and cheese.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Add eggs, beat until smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish, top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes and eggs.
Add celery, onion and Italian dressing; thoroughly mix.
Place paper towel over bowl (to absorb moisture) and chill until hour before serving.
Add Miracle Whip and thoroughly mix.

title: sean johnson's orange julius
directions: Put orange juice in the blender.
Use the 6 ounce orange juice can to measure out the ice cubes, milk and water.
Combine all ingredients in the blender and blend until mixed and smooth.

title: sausage corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Partially brown sausage in large skillet; reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Grease a 10-inch skillet. Preheat oven.
Combine egg, milk and sausage drippings.
Stir in sausage and corn meal.
Blend well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Mash potatoes until smooth.
Add cream cheese, 4 tablespoons of butter, garlic salt, pepper and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Gradually add milk, mixing until smooth.
Turn potato mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Dot the top with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, then at 375° for 30 minutes longer.

title: chocolate oatmeal chippers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually add combined flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes, until set.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.
Store tightly covered.

title: osso buco
directions: Trim fat from veal.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; coat with flour.
Cook over medium heat until brown on all sides, about 20 minutes.
Stir in broth, wine, garlic and bay leaf.
Heat to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Remove veal; skim fat from broth.
Return veal to broth.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Sprinkle veal with parsley and lemon peel.
Heat to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Serve on spaghetti; sprinkle with cheese.

title: koone pasta
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Cook noodles until done; drain.
Mix hamburger, soup, mushrooms and egg noodles.
Add seasonings to taste.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Fold in the berries.
Grease tins well.
Grease tops of tin, too.
Pile batter high in cups.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°. Cool in pans for 30 minutes before removing.

title: slimming sippers
directions: In a blender container combine juice cocktail and berries. Cover; blend until almost smooth.
Sieve mixture; return to blender.
Discard seeds.
Add ice cubes.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Serves 5.
Low in calories, high in flavor!

title: sugar cookies(big, old fashioned)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to batter. Chill several hours before rolling out dough.
Use 1-pound coffee can (empty) as cookie cutter.
Cut out cookies; sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Do not let cookies brown around edges.

title: crab cakes(yields 4 servings)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Shape into cakes.
Brown on both sides in shortening in skillet.
Drain.

title: one-rise monkey bread
directions: Grease 12-cup
fluted tube pan or 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl, blend 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast, water, margarine and
egg
at
low
speed
until
moistened.
Beat
3 minutes at medium
speed.
Stir
in
remaining flour by hand. Knead dough
on floured surface until smooth, about 1 minute. Press or
roll dough
to 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Using sharp knife,
cut	dough into diamond-shaped pieces by cutting into 2-inch strips diagonally across dough.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Shape into a ball. Roll in the finely chopped nuts. Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pineapple and lemon juice.
Fold in the bread cubes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and milk.
Melt oleo in large size casserole dish in oven.
Pour mixture over oleo.
Use berries or fruit plus sugar and a little lemon juice mixed together.
Pour on batter.
Bake in 375° oven 35 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain into thin slices.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger; add beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in large frypan.
Add beef and toss over high heat until brown.
If meat is not tender, cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Toss until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add to pan; stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: apple date pudding cake
directions: Mix all together in one bowl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pineapple bread casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cream margarine and sugar; beat in eggs. Add pineapple and 1 cup juice.
Stir in bread cubes.
Place in greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and water.
Add flour, baking soda, vanilla and crushed pineapple.
Bake
in
a
greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool and top with cream cheese icing.
Makes
to
12 servings.

title: crisco creamy frosting
directions: Put into bowl and beat until creamy.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together. Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Blend.
Turn into 3 9-inch round pans lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool a few minutes in pans, then turn out and cool on wire racks.
Cake will be very brown as it bakes.
Fill
layers and spread top and sides with Cream Cheese frosting.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vinegar, mustard and garlic with about 3 ounces of cheese.
Mash cheese well.
Slowly add oil while mixing with electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in remaining cheese with spoon.
Chill.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place 3 cups of the lettuce in bottom of a large bowl. Sprinkle with a little sugar, salt and pepper.
Layer eggs on top of lettuce in bowl.
Sprinkle generously with salt.
Layer in order:
peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over the top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover; refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Garnish
with green onion and sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Toss before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: castigliola shrimp
directions: *Wash lemons; squeeze juice in pot and put lemon rind in too.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, chicken soup, onion, pimento and sour cream.
Melt 3/4 stick oleo in skillet; add about 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm stuffing; sauteed.
Line baking dish with buttered stuffing (save 1/2 crumbs for top).
Pour mixture in and cover with balance of crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: alphabet salad
directions: Drain and refrigerate fruit.
Save juice.
Combine sugar, flour and salt; add to juice.
Add eggs.
Heat to slow boiling. Cook 1 minute.
Add to cooked pasta.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Simmer potatoes until tender.
Saute celery, green pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Make gravy with 3 tablespoons of butter, flour, seasonings and broth.
Pour other ingredients into casserole dish.

title: dill carrots
directions: Wash and
trim	carrots.
Cut
into
small
strips
and blanch for 2
to
3 minutes.
Rinse in cold water.
Make brine of vinegar, water,
sugar and salt.
Bring this to a boil.
In each jar, put 2 cloves of garlic and pack with carrots.	Place small pieces of
dill
on
top and pour boiling brine over and seal.

title: black bean picadillo
directions: Place beans in a large saucepan.
Add water to cover by 2-inches.
Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and cover.
Let stand 1 hour.
Part freeze steak (30 minutes) and cut very thin across grain.
Cook in olive oil in large skillet until no longer pink.
Stirring, add onion and garlic.
Cook until soft. Drain beans and discard liquid.
Return beans to pan and add broth and water.
Stir steak mixture into beans.
Add hot pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to slow simmer.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Reduce heat to slow simmer. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Discard bay leaf and pepper.
Stir in tomato sauce and olives.
Simmer uncovered until near dry.

title: fresh green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in bottom of greased casserole.
Layer soup, cheese, eggs, cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: taco fry bread
directions: Mix enough warm water to flour to be able to knead dough. Also add oil to flour.
Let set for 2 hours.
Just before meal, break off pieces, approximately 1/2 cup and spread out and fry in hot 400°
oil.
Makes about 12 tacos, plate-sized.
Layer other ingredients on the fry bread.
Fun to do and eat.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs; mix with sugar and melted oleo.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture; mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into an ungreased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let set until firm.
Serve with ice cream.

title: strawberry whips
directions: Bake in muffin tins in hot oven (375°) for 20 or 30 minutes. When cool, cut out centers of cakes and fill.

title: low-fat spinach, pasta and chicken casserole
directions: Cook pasta of your choice according to package directions and drain.
Place spinach on paper towels, squeeze out excess liquid. Coat large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; and oil and place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saute until tender.
Add chicken and cook until chicken loses its pinkish color, stirring constantly.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Add next 5 ingredients; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, continue to stir.
Combine pasta, spinach, chicken mixture and 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Add 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields about 8 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine salmon, crumbs, chopped onion, butter and salt.
Combine milk and egg; add to salmon mixture and mix thoroughly.
Shape into a loaf on a greased shallow baking or in 7 1/2 x 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: golden pennies salad
directions: Heat the last 6 ingredients and pour over the remaining ingredients.
Let stand several hours or overnight.
Will keep 3 weeks in fridge.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice the cucumbers and onions thin. Add the sour cream, parsley, oil and vinegar.
Blend in the sugar to taste, salt and pepper.
Great side dish for dinner or picnics.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Combine remaining ingredients and toss just before serving.

title: mom's honey bun cake
directions: Mix all together in one bowl.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour or less.

title: corn delight casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until soft.
Mix with eggs and corn muffin mix.
Mix in corn and pour into greased casserole.
Mix sour cream and cheese and put on top of corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: spaghetti marco polo
directions: Cook spaghetti, al dente; set aside.
Saute oil and 1/2 garlic clove.
Add walnuts, olives, pimentos, basil and parsley.
Add pepper to taste.
Add cream and cheese.
Cook until hot and melted.
Toss with spaghetti, adding cream and cheese as desired. Serve immediately.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Add soups, 1 cup milk and cheese. Add more milk to make thin.

title: archie's pie crust
directions: Mix with mixer.
Divide in 2 equal portions.
Wrap in wax paper and put in freezer for 15 minutes.
Take out of freezer. Press into pie pan using wax paper.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Good used with chocolate pie.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix
soda and buttermilk and let stand.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream
oleo,
sugar and shortening until fluffy. Add
egg yolks and beat well, about 4 minutes fast speed.
Add vanilla. Add flour alternating with milk.
Fold in coconut and pecans,
add egg white.
Bake in 3 greased and floured pans at 325° for 25 minutes or when top is firm and brown.

title: hamburg balls
directions: Combine hamburg, onions, green pepper, corn meal, seasonings, milk and egg.
Blend thoroughly.
Form into 12 balls.
Roll in flour.
Brown in hot Spry in skillet.
Add remaining flour and tomatoes.
Cover and cook on low heat for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: corn light bread
directions: Finish thickening with meal until a little thicker than egg bread.
Grease stem pan and paper the bottom.
Put in stem pan. Cook over hot water for 1 1/2 hours, then bake until brown, about 30 minutes, at 450°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into shell(s).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; heat to boiling.
Pour over popped corn; stir.
Make into balls or spread flat on buttered cookie sheet.
Use different flavors of jello for different colors.

title: dorothy's scalloped potatoes
directions: Place in layers in
a 3 quart casserole.
Dot about 1/4 pound oleo on top.
Add 2 cups milk (might use less).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then
at
350°	for
minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients well. Roll into small balls, then roll balls into powdered sugar. Put on waxed paper.
Let them set out overnight, then put in a closed container.
If you want them for Christmas, make them in October or November.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan in the order listed, covering the top with dots of butter. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry; mix all ingredients.
Serve with corn chips.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix and beat the sifted and boiled ingredients and then add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for about 20 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise, just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place potatoes in a microsafe dish or pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped parsley, chives or sage.
Microwave at High power for 10 minutes, rearranging the potatoes after 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese. Microwave 4 to 6 minutes longer.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix together and bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Heat chili sauce, lemon juice and grape jelly in saucepan until jelly dissolves.
Pour over meatballs and continue baking for 1 hour at 350° in roasting pan.
When done, can be put into crock-pot on low for easy serving.

title: seashell pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together all ingredients until well mixed. Cover and Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: alabama cornbread
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and stir together well.
Bake at 400° until done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Put in microwave or oven-safe dish.
Stir in one can of soup.
Top with the sliced cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Stir; serve hot.

title: layer cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together. Add eggs and beat well, then add vanilla. Mix baking powder, salt and flour together. Add milk and flour, small amounts at a time of each; do not beat much after putting flour in. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add carrots and stir well.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: candied red apples
directions: You will need 6 wooden skewers.

title: beef marinade
directions: Fork meat and sprinkle with tenderizer.
Mix other ingredients and pour over meat.
Keep in refrigerator 12 hours and set out 6 hours.
Bake or grill as desired.

title: green bean casserole supreme
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in margarine until lightly browned. Add flour, blending well.
Add sour cream and heat over low heat, stirring until mixture thickens slightly.
Add green beans, salt and pepper.
Pour into 10-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine the finely crushed crackers and the melted butter. Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the ice cream and instant pudding; mix well and spread over crust.
Can be kept overnight in the refrigerator.
When ready to serve, use Cool Whip.

title: low cholesterol chicken rice casserole
directions: Brown chicken strips, onion and garlic in oil until done.
Add tomatoes, sauce seasonings and ground pepper.
Bring to a boil. Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Serve.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour cake mix into mixing bowl and add water, pudding, eggs and sour cream.
Blend well and add the chocolate chips.
Pour into greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: walnut pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar and baking powder. Fold in Ritz crackers and nuts.
Butter and flour pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve with whipped cream, ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare diced ingredients.
Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add frozen juice and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: mexican dip
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Spread cream cheese in the bottom of a pie plate or square pan. Pour salsa over the cream cheese. Sprinkle shredded cheese over the salsa. Bake in the oven for 30 minutes or until the cheese starts to bubble.

title: hearty beef, broccoli and potato casserole
directions: Place potato rounds or Tater Tots on bottom and up sides of an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef in large chunks; drain.
Place beef, broccoli, 1/2 can of Durkee onions and tomato in potato shell. Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: old-fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour and milk; set aside.
Melt butter in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Add undrained peaches.
Pour flour mixture over peaches.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, approximately 35 minutes.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray baking pan.
Dip chicken in margarine.
Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: cherry coke salad(this goes well with meats.)
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries (add enough water if necessary to make 2 cups).
Heat the juices until boiling, and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Stir in beverage.
Add well drained fruit.
Pour into bowl or oblong pan and refrigerate until set.

title: vanilla wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl with mixer at low speed, beat all ingredients with a rubber spatula.

Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake cookies 10 to 12 minutes until edges of cookies are browned. With pancake turner, remove cookies to wire racks to cool.
Store cookies in a tightly covered container to use within one week.

title: pecan glazed pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet pan to 375°.
In large bowl, using a wire whisk, whisk together eggs, pumpkin, milk, 3/4 cup sugar and pumpkin pie spice.
Place frozen pie crust on preheated baking sheet. Pour filling into crust.
Bake 40 minutes. In small bowl, combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar, pecans and melted butter. Crumble over top of partially baked pie.
Bake an additional 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: parmesan-walnut bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together the egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring until combined.
Stir in 3/4 cup of nuts. Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle the remaining nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove loaf from pan; cool completely on a wire rack. Wrap and store overnight before slicing.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Combine sugar, water and cinnamon hearts in a large pan. Heat over medium heat until cinnamon hearts are melted. Stirring constantly.
Add apple halves and cook until tender.
(makes a pretty Christmas dish.
Oil of Cinnamon and green food coloring may be used to get green cinnamon apples.

title: crab stuffing
directions: Mix well.
Use for stuffed shrimp or fish.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour and next 4 ingredients.
Add 1 cup water and mushrooms with liquid.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini. Sift together dry ingredients with flour, then add and mix well. Add nuts.
Pour into 2 bread pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: honey limeade
directions: Put the lime juice in a pitcher.
Add the honey, sugar and water.
Stir until the sugar dissolves.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve over ice.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Let set 2 hours.

title: old-fashioned soda biscuits
directions: Add the baking soda to the bowl along with the flour and then mix, shape, and bake biscuits at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves, eggs and vanilla.
Melt butter in milk.
Pour into potato mixture, stirring.
Beat gently with beater until well blended and smooth.
Turn into pastry-lined pie pan with edges of pastry fluted.
Bake in very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until silver knife comes out clean.

title: ozark pancake(ethnic background-german immigrants)
directions: Beat 3 eggs until foaming.
Add flour and beat again.
Add milk and beat again.
Heat iron skillet on stove; get it very hot. Melt quickly 2 1/2 tablespoons butter or substitute.
Turn off heat.
Pour into skillet.
Put in 450° preheated oven.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: ground beef supreme
directions: Brown meat and onion (and celery if desired).
Blend margarine, stuffing and water.
In a 2-quart casserole, layer the meat mixture with stuffing, 1/2 meat, all stuffing, remaining 1/2 meat.
Blend 1/4 cup water with soup and pour over casserole. Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 5 to 6.

title: low-fat granola
directions: Combine oats, Grape Nuts and peanuts.
Combine vegetable oil, water, salt, vanilla and syrup.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Mix to coat.
Spread on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Cool and add raisins.
Store in airtight containers. Makes 32 (1/4 cup) servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender.
Fry bacon and add onion, sugar and flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add vinegar and water to the mixture over fire.
Add parsley (for color), salt and pepper to taste.
Pour liquid over diced potatoes.
Let sit in the refrigerator overnight.
Warm before serving.
Serves 6.

title: muscadine pie
directions: Mash and cook muscadines in their own juice (no water) until tender.
Squeeze out juice.
Put juice in 3-quart saucepan with 1 cup sugar.
Put 3/4 cup sugar in bowl with cornstarch and Butter Buds.
Stir until thoroughly mixed (no lumps).
Put juice and sugar on stove eye.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Cook until thickened; cool. Bake crust.
Mix Cool Whip and pie mixture together.
Pour into cool pie shells.
